0and%20achievements.%20What%20are%20the%20other%20things%20that%20set%20him%20apart%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPatrick%20Olivelle%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20main%20thing%20is%20that%20he%20exposes%20himself%2C%20he%20opens%20himself%20out%20in%20his%20writing%20to%20his%20people%2C%20in%20a%20way%20that%20most%20kings%20or%20even%20politicians%20rarely%20do.%20He%20makes%20himself%20vulnerable%2C%20he%20is%20strong%20enough%20to%20say%20that%20he%E2%80%99s%20sorry%20about%20various%20things%20that%20he%20did%20in%20his%20life.%20Instead%20of%20boasting%20about%20his%20conquests%2C%20for%20example%20the%20parallels%20you%20find%20in%20Persia%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Persian%20kings%20who%20say%20how%20many%20lands%20they%20have%20conquered%20%E2%80%93%20the%20only%20time%20he%20talks%20about%20his%20conquest%20is%20where%20he%20talks%20about%20his%20conquest%20of%20Kalinga%2C%20which%20is%20todays%20Odisha%20area.%20He%20says%20that%20in%20a%20sense%20of%20regret%20rather%20than%20of%20boasting%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20I%20was%20just%20thinking%20the%20other%20day%20that%20if%20he%20had%20not%20written%20about%20it%2C%20we%20as%20historians%20would%20have%20no%20idea%20that%20such%20a%20battle%20ever%20took%20place%2C%20because%20there%20is%20no%20other%20historical%20evidence%20for%20the%20Mauryans%20going%20and%20conquering%20this%20independent%20state%20of%20Kalinga.%20So%20in%20a%20sense%2C%20it%20is%20his%20own%20words%20that%20come%20and%20give%20us%20a%20sense%20of%20how%20he%E2%80%99s%20regretful%20because%20150%2C000%20people%20were%20killed%2C%20over%20that%20many%20were%20deported%2C%20and%20the%20same%20amount%20died%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20war.%20So%20all%20of%20that%2C%20although%C2%A0we%20may%20want%20to%20as%20historians%20say%20that%20these%20numbers%20may%20be%20maybe%20fudged%2C%20maybe%20rounded%20out%20and%20all%20that%2C%20yet%20a%20large%20number%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20think%20of%20it%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20terms%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20not%20saying%20that%20this%20is%20true%20for%20the%20past%2C%20%5Bbut%5D%20if%20we%20think%20of%20today%E2%80%99s%20terms%2C%20that%20would%20qualify%20for%20genocide.%20You%20find%20the%20same%20thing%20with%20Alexander%20when%20he%20conquered%2C%20many%20of%20his%20conquests%20were%20genocide%3B%20%5Bas%20was%5D%20the%20Carthage%20during%20the%20Roman%20times.%20Genocide%20was%20common%2C%20what%20we%20call%20genocide%20happened%20in%20the%20past.%20It%20was%20not%20a%20rare%20occasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20anyway%2C%20in%20this%20sense%20Ashoka%2C%20I%20think%2C%20is%20unique%20in%20world%20history%2C%20because%20not%20just%20in%20ancient%20history%20but%20even%20in%20modern%20history%2C%20rarely%20do%20we%20find%20politicians%20or%20people%20in%20power%20saying%20they%E2%80%99re%20sorry%20for%20things%20they%20have%20done%20in%20the%20past.%20Also%20there%20are%20his%20writings%20with%20regard%20to%20moral%20philosophy%2C%20how%20people%20should%20behave%3B%20there%20is%20nothing%20in%C2%A0Ashoka%E2%80%99s%20writings%20that%20deal%20with%20governance%20as%20such.%20He%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20talk%20about%20taxation%2C%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20talk%20about%20how%20he%20gets%20his%20money%2C%20none%20of%20those%20is%20there.%20So%20that%E2%80%99s%2C%20in%20that%20sense%2C%20unique.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJS%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Are%20these%20some%20of%20the%20reasons%20for%20why%20you%20chose%20this%20to%20be%20the%20first%20book%20in%20this%20series%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERamachandra%20Guha%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20No%2C%20well%20I%E2%80%99ll%20come%20to%20that%2C%20but%20just%20listening%20to%20Patrick%20speak%20and%20on%20the%20question%20of%20kings%20being%20reflective%20about%20their%20style%20of%20rule%2C%20including%20the%20errors%20and%20mistakes%20and%20deficiencies%20in%20the%20style%20of%20rule%20%E2%80%93%20listening%20to%20Patrick%20I%20was%20thinking%20of%20say%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%2C%20who%20greatly%20admired%20Ashoka%20and%20who%20was%20a%20wonderful%20stylist%20like%20Ashoka%2C%20though%20in%20the%20English%20language%2C%20and%20who%20wrote%20meditatively%2C%20reflectively%2C%20sometimes%20self-critically%20about%20himself%2C%20but%20only%20before%20he%20became%20prime%20minister.%20So%20his%20autobiography%20or%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Discovery%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E.%20But%20then%20from%20%E2%80%9947%20to%20%E2%80%9964%2C%20even%20in%20his%20personal%20correspondence%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20hard%20to%20find%20him%20saying%20%E2%80%98maybe%20I%20should%20have%20done%20this%20differently%E2%80%99.%20Right%2C%20so%20I%20think%20in%20that%20sense%2C%20listening%20to%20Patrick%20that%20strikes%20me.%20Or%20if%20you%20look%20at%20Churchill%2C%20who%20was%20again%20a%20wonderful%20stylist%2C%20he%20got%20the%20Nobel%20prize%20for%20literature%2C%20I%20think%20not%20unjustifiably.%20However%2C%20as%20prime%20minister%20when%20he%20wrote%20the%20history%20of%20his%20prime%20ministerial%20term%2C%20it%20was%20self%20justificatory.%20And%20he%20obviously%20played%20an%20important%20role%20as%20prime%C2%A0minister%20of%20Britain%20in%20defeating%20Hitler.%20But%20he%20exaggerated%20that%20role%20and%20maybe%20minimised%20the%20role%20of%20other%20people%2C%20other%20allies%2C%20the%20Soviets%2C%20the%20Americans%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20So%20I%20think%20that%E2%80%99s%20why%20listening%20to%20Patrick%20was%20fascinating%20to%20see%20what%20Ashoka%20special.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20delighted%20that%20this%20is%20the%20first%20volume%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20so%20beautifully%20crafted%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20so%20sensitive%20to%20ruins%2C%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20partly%20an%20accident.%20I%20mean%20the%20series%20was%20conceptualised%2C%20and%20the%20idea%20of%20the%20series%20was%20that%20the%20general%20reader%20likes%20to%20consume%20history%20in%20the%20form%20of%20biographies.%20But%20professional%20historians%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20disparage%20biography%20%E2%80%93%20that%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20spend%20so%20much%20time%20writing%20about%20one%20person.%20We%E2%80%99d%20rather%20write%20about%20politics%20and%20kingship%20in%20ancient%20India%20rather%20than%20one%20ruler.%20So%20I%20was%20very%20keen%20to%20bridge%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPatrick%20and%20I%20were%20in%20correspondence%20about%20some%20other%20things%20and%20then%20I%20just%20asked%20Patrick%2C%20%E2%80%98Have%20you%20ever%20thought%20of%20writing%20on%20Ashoka%3F%20You%E2%80%99ve%20lived%20with%20that%20period%2C%20those%20sources%20all%20your%20life%20but%20you%E2%80%99ve%20written%20about%20law%2C%20you%E2%80%99ve%20written%20about%20religion%2C%20you%E2%80%99ve%20written%20about%20social%20structure%2C%20you%E2%80%99ve%20written%20textual%20studies%2C%20you%E2%80%99ve%20done%20translations.%E2%80%99%20So%20the%20idea%20struck%20him%20and%20he%20produced%20his%20magnificent%20book.%20I%E2%80%99m%20really%20delighted%20that%20this%20is%2C%20I%20mean%20Patrick%20is%20Sri%20Lankan.%20So%20I%20told%20him%20that%20this%20is%20like%20a%20combination%20of%2C%20and%20we%20are%20both%20cricket%20fans%2C%20so%20I%20said%20this%20is%20kind%20of%20Jayasuriya%20opening%20the%20innings%20but%20there%20will%20be%20Ranatunga%2C%20Aravinda%20de%20Silva%2C%20and%20others%20to%20follow%20up.%20So%20there%E2%80%99ll%20be%20some%20very%20good%20historians%E2%80%99%20writing%20on%20maybe%20modern%20subjects.%20So%20the%20second%20book%20which%20will%20appear%20in%20three%20months%20is%20by%20Chitralekha%20Zutshi%2C%20who%E2%80%99s%20the%20leading%20historian%20of%20modern%20Kashmir%2C%20on%20Sheikh%20Abdullah.%20The%20third%20book%20is%20on%20Kamala%20Devi%20Chattapadhyay%20by%20a%20very%20fine%20American%20historian%20Nico%20Slate.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20think%20this%20has%20set%20a%20very%20high%20bar%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20sure%20that%20I%20mean%20Patrick%20is%20%3Cem%3Esui%20generis%3C%2Fem%3E%20because%20of%20the%20range%20of%20his%20work%2C%20but%20also%20he%20has%20been%20a%20scholar%20for%20more%20than%2050%20years.%20So%20the%20second%20and%20the%20third%20volumes%20are%20written%20by%20people%20who%20are%20still%20maturing%20but%20have%20done%20the%20first%20stint.%20So%20I%20think%20Patrick%E2%80%99s%20book%20is%20just%20riveting%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20so%20insightful%2C%20and%20I%20think%20to%20start%20this%20series%20with%20this%20book%20%E2%80%93%20I%20will%20encourage%20the%20writers%20to%20follow%20to%20fulfil%20these%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJS%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Early%20on%20in%20the%20book%20you%20spend%20some%20time%20establishing%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20likely%20that%20Ashoka%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20rather%20multicultural%20court%20and%20household.%20How%20rare%20was%20that%20at%20the%20time%20and%20what%20kind%20of%20impact%20do%20you%20think%20that%20had%20later%20when%20he%20became%20the%20ruler%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Writing%20a%20biography%20of%20a%20person%20who%20lived%202%2C300%20years%20or%20so%20ago%2C%20with%20so%20little%20to%20go%E2%80%A6%20Ram%20had%20talked%20about%20his%20friend%20and%20mentor%2C%20Boyle.%20The%20three%20laws%20of%20Boyle%2C%20I%20violate%20all%20of%20them.%20Because%2C%20I%20mean%2C%20you%20work%20with%20what%20you%20have%2C%20rather%20than%20what%20you%20wish%20you%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJS%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20What%20are%20the%20three%20laws%3F%20Can%20you%20quickly%20tell%20us%20what%20the%20three%20laws%20are%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20I%20will%20tell%20you%20what%20the%20three%20laws%20are%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20give%20a%20brief%20background.%20My%20first%20biography%20was%20of%20a%20man%20called%20Verrier%20Elwin%2C%20I%20came%20to%20Gandhi%20much%20later.%20And%20when%20I%20was%20writing%20it%2C%20I%20was%20lucky%20to%20be%20in%20the%20same%20institute%20in%20Berlin%20with%20the%20great%20biography%20of%20Goethe%2C%20Nicholas%20Boyle%2C%20Professor%20of%20Cambridge.%20He%20was%20sort%20of%20like%20a%20mentor%20to%20me%2C%20he%20really%20made%20my%20Elwin%20biography%20much%20better%20than%20it%20was.%20He%20didn%E2%80%99t%20call%20it%20three%20laws%20but%20his%20three%20laws%20were%3A%20One%2C%20first%20look%20for%20sources%20other%20than%20those%20emanating%20from%20your%20principal%20character.%20So%20Elwin%20wrote%2040%20books%2C%20400%20newspaper%20articles%2C%204%2C000%20letters%20and%20likewise%20with%20Nehru%2C%20Gandhi%20or%20Ambedkar.%20You%20can%20write%20the%20whole%20book%20based%20on%20what%20they%20have%20said%20%E2%80%93%20so%20look%20for%20sources%20that%20come%20from%20a%20second%20party%2C%20a%20third%20party%2C%20a%2010th%20party%20which%20may%20be%20a%20friend%20or%20admirer.%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20first%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20law%20is%20that%20the%20relationship%20with%20secondary%20characters%20illuminates%20the%20principal%20character.%20So%20if%20you%20write%20about%20Ambedkar%2C%20there%20will%20be%20a%C2%A0light%20on%20Gandhi%2C%20right%3F%20If%20you%20look%20at%20their%20interaction%20or%20Nehru%20and%20the%20Hindu%20right%2C%20that%20is%20the%20second%20law.%20Pay%20adequate%20attention%20to%20the%20secondary%20characters%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20just%20focus%20on%20the%20principal%20character.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20law%20is%20always%20go%20chronologically.%20A%20life%20is%20lived%20forward%20but%20understood%20backwards%2C%20but%20he%20has%20lived%20from%20day%20to%20day.%20So%20for%20example%2C%20in%20the%20case%20of%20Elwin%2C%20he%20was%20a%20celibate%20because%20of%20Gandhi%2C%20but%20then%20he%20became%20flagrantly%20exalting%20sex.%20But%20let%20that%20slowly%20develop.%20Don%E2%80%99t%20say%20%E2%80%93%20because%20the%20reader%20is%20saying%20%E2%80%98what%20an%20idiot%20to%20follow%20Gandhi%20in%20%3Cem%3Ebrahmacharya%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98%2C%20and%20you%20as%20an%20admirer%20want%20to%20say%2C%20actually%20he%20later%20changed%20his%20mind%2C%20but%C2%A0don%E2%80%99t.%20Keep%20the%20reader%20in%20suspense.%20If%20you%E2%80%99re%20a%20sociologist%20or%20an%20economist%2C%20you%20tend%20to%20state%20your%20thesis%20quite%20early.%20This%20is%20a%20book%20about%20inequality%2C%20so%20the%20reader%20already%20knows%20the%20inequality%20is%20growing%20or%20something%2C%20right%3F%20Here%20the%20suspense%20because%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20life%20is%20%E2%80%93%20unpredictable%2C%20unexpected.%20So%20these%20are%20the%20three%20laws%20which%20in%20retrospect%20I%20realise%20only%20apply%C2%A0to%20the%20biographer%20of%20a%20modern%20person%20where%20the%20sources%20are%20rich%20enough.%20So%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20Patrick%20means%20when%20he%20says%20that%20he%20violates%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Anyway%20getting%20back%20to%20your%20original%20question%20about%20multiculturalism%2C%20this%20is%20where%20a%20biography%20like%20what%20I%20did%20has%20to%20have%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20imagination%20and%20maybe%20even%20trying%20to%20imagine%20what%20would%20have%20been%20there%2C%20to%20draw%20out%20perhaps%20sometimes%20more%20than%20is%20permitted%20from%20the%20few%20sources%20we%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%20basically%2C%20Alexander%E2%80%99s%20conquest%20of%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20West%20Asia%2C%20all%20the%20way%20into%20what%20is%20today%20Pakistan%2C%20was%20a%20major%20event.%20Not%20just%20that%20he%20came%20and%20conquered%2C%20but%20he%20left%20behind%20Greek%20culture%20and%20Greek%20kingdoms%20from%20Egypt%20to%20what%20is%20today%20Afghanistan.%20The%20Seleucid%20Empire%20was%20the%20one%20with%20which%20Chandragupta%20Maurya%20dealt%20with.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20wonderful%20book%20written%20about%20the%20Seleucid%20Empire%20recently%20and%20what%20this%20person%20talks%20about%20is%20the%20so-called%20Indus%20Treatise%2C%20the%20Treaty%20of%20the%20Indus%20between%20Chandragupta%20and%20the%20Seleucus%20First%2C%20which%20established%20boundaries%20of%20autonomous%20kingdoms%20which%20had%20never%20existed.%20If%20you%20look%20at%20our%20old%20great%20friend%2C%20Kautilya%20in%20his%20%3Cem%3EArthashastra%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20he%20talks%20about%20the%20king%20as%20forever%20wishing%20to%20conquer.%20In%20Sanskrit%20he%20calls%20it%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Evijgishu%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20one%20who%20wishes%20to%20conquer.%20That%20is%20the%20defining%20element%20of%20a%20king.%20This%20was%20contravened%20in%20this%20emergent%20concept%20of%20bounded%20kingdoms%20and%20this%20became%20part%20of%20the%20Mauryan%20Empire.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20after%20this%20treaty%2C%20in%20all%20likelihood%20there%20was%20the%20exchange%20of%20women%2C%20which%20was%20normally%20done.%20So%20Seleucid%E2%80%99s%20Prince%20from%20the%20family%20%E2%80%93%20may%20not%20be%20his%20own%20daughter%20but%20somebody%20%E2%80%93%20who%20came%20to%20Chandragupta%E2%80%99s.%20Clearly%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20Greek%20influence%20there%2C%20right%3F%20Ashoka%20may%20have%20been%20a%20young%20boy%20then%2C%20maybe%20three%2C%20four%20or%20five%2C%20when%20Chandragupta%20died.%20So%20there%20was%20a%20Greek%20presence%20in%20the%20Chandragupta.%20Then%20his%20own%20father%20may%20have%20had%20Greek%20wives%2C%20if%20you%20may%20want%20to%20call%20it%20that.%20In%20my%20imagination%20at%20least%2C%20I%20think%20there%20is%20a%20multiculturalism%2C%20and%20in%20his%20own%20thinking%20when%20he%20got%20his%20inscriptions%20translated%20and%20inscribed%20in%20Greek%20and%20in%20Aramaic.%20Strangely%20enough%2C%20Aramaic%20was%20not%20really%20spoken%20by%20anybody.%20It%20was%20the%20Persian%20language%20of%20the%20Chancery%2C%20so%20only%20some%20people%20knew%20that%20but%20it%20became%20iconic.%20So%20two%20iconic%20languages%20%E2%80%93%20Greek%2C%20the%20great%20Alexander%E2%80%99s%2C%20and%20then%20Aramaic.%20I%20think%20that%20could%20have%20been%20done%20only%20by%20a%20person%20who%20had%20that%20larger%20vision%20that%20comes%20from%20being%20brought%20up%20in%20a%20multicultural%2C%20what%20we%20would%20call%20today%2C%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FkXeiy3lgNmI%3Fsi%3DIc_ll7721lYz2MCH%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJS%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20You%20mentioned%20earlier%20about%20Kalinga%20and%20his%20expression%20of%20remorse%20because%20of%C2%A0the%20destruction%20that%20that%20caused.%20But%20then%20you%20also%20say%20that%20that%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20we%20call%20him%20a%20pacifist.%20So%20first%20how%20would%20you%20explain%20that%2C%20and%20also%20how%20much%20evidence%20is%20there%20for%20this%20common%20conception%20that%20it%20was%20that%20battle%20that%20then%20led%20him%20to%20embrace%20Buddhism%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Yes%2C%20I%20talk%20about%20that%20a%20little%20bit%20in%20trying%20to%20draw%20a%20chronology.%20Again%20very%20speculative%2C%20I%20grant%20it.%20But%20all%20this%20happened%20I%20think%20within%20a%20period%20of%20about%20two%20years%2C%20even%20less.%20So%20there%20was%20a%20moment%20when%20he%20turned.%20He%20was%2C%20he%20himself%20says%20in%20his%20first%20minor%20inscription%2C%20that%20he%20was%20a%20Buddhist%2C%20you%20know%3F%20That%20he%20followed%20that.%20But%20he%20was%20a%20so-so%20Buddhist%2C%20right%3F%20He%20was%20from%20Magadha%2C%20after%20all%3B%20that%20was%20the%20place%20where%20Jainism%20and%20Buddhism%20were%20thriving.%20But%20then%20he%20says%20that%20he%20went%20to%20see%20the%20monks.%20Doesn%E2%80%99t%20say%20one%20monk%20or%20many%2C%20it%20says%20a%20sangh%2C%20right%3F%20So%20that%20monastic%20order%20after%20which%20he%20became%2C%20he%20says%2C%20zealous%20in%20this.%20And%20that%20was%20the%20time%20when%20he%20says%20he%20became%20an%20%3Cem%3Eupasaka%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20is%20a%20technical%20Buddhist%20term%20for%20a%20committed%20Buddhist.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20at%20the%20same%20time%20if%20you%20go%20with%20the%20chronology%2C%20you%20find%20that%20the%20Battle%20of%20Kalinga%20was%20probably%20done%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20or%20so%20before%20this%20time.%20So%20putting%20two%20and%20two%20together%20and%20arriving%20at%20five%2C%20one%20can%20maybe%20come%20up%20with%20a%20chronology%20that%20links%2C%20at%20least%20chronologically%2C%20the%20two%20events.%20Whether%20they%20are%20connected%20in%20his%20own%20mind%2C%20in%20his%20own%20life%2C%20that%20of%20course%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20say%20anywhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJS%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EYou%20also%20say%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20more%20appropriate%20to%20refer%20to%20him%20as%20a%20king%20who%20was%20a%20Buddhist%20rather%20than%20a%20Buddhist%20King.%20So%20I%E2%80%99m%20asking%20where%20would%20you%20draw%20that%20balance%2C%20especially%20given%20the%20centrality%20of%20moral%20philosophy%20which%20was%20first%20based%20more%20on%20Buddhism%20and%20then%20later%2C%20on%20not%20referring%20to%20a%20particular%20religion%20but%20just%20%3Cem%3Edharma%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20a%20more%20inclusive%20idea.%20So%20given%20the%20centrality%20of%20that%20in%20his%20messaging%20where%20do%20you%20draw%20that%20line%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Right%20so%20again%2C%20taking%20the%20few%20clues%20that%20we%20have%2C%20I%20try%20to%20say%20that%20if%20the%20king%20who%20wrote%20the%20first%20minor%20rock%20inscription%20which%20is%20the%20most%20widespread%2C%20especially%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20in%20the%20South.%20If%20that%20person%20was%20Ashoka%20throughout%20his%20life%2C%20he%20would%20have%20been%20a%20Buddhist%20king.%20But%20that%20didn%E2%80%99t%20happen.%20I%20tried%20to%20imagine%20what%20may%20have%20happened.%20After%20writing%20this%2C%20sometime%20in%20June%20of%20a%20year%2C%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20tell%20you%20exactly%20what%20it%20was%2C%20then%20within%20a%20year%20or%20two%20he%20starts%20writing%20about%20dharma.%20So%20I%20sort%20of%20imagine%20that%20some%20intervention%20took%20place.%20He%20went%20home%20%E2%80%93%20he%20had%20been%20travelling%20for%20eight%20months%20during%20which%20time%20he%20was%20imitating%20the%20lifestyle%20of%20a%20monk%20on%20his%20travels%20%E2%80%93%20he%20came%20home.%20Maybe%20somebody%20got%20to%20him%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%98Hey%20guy%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%20this.%20You%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20a%20Buddhist%20and%20rule%20over%20this%20immense%20kingdom.%20There%E2%80%99s%20something%20wrong%20here.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOr%20he%20had%20second%20thoughts.%20Maybe%20he%20thought%20I%20want%20to%20do%20something%20larger%20than%20Buddhism%2C%20better%20than%20Buddhism%2C%20more%20important%20than%20Buddhism.%20There%20could%20have%20been%20many%20ways%20in%20which%20we%20can%20slice%20this%2C%20but%20ultimately%20he%20changed%2C%20he%20changed%20over%20a%20period%2C%20short%20again%2C%20two%20years%20at%20the%20most.%20When%20he%20then%20started%20writing%20about%20dharma%20and%20in%20all%20his%20major%20rock%20inscriptions%2C%2014%20of%20them%2C%20he%20never%20once%20mentioned%20Buddhism%20except%20in%20passing%2C%20to%20refer%20it%20to%20among%20others%2C%20Jains%20and%20Brahmins%20and%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%20he%20never%20once%20against%20brings%20Buddhism%20into%20the%20focus%20of%20his%20message%2C%20which%20tells%20me%2C%20from%20here%20to%20here%20was%20different%2C%20and%20this%20is%20what%20defined%20much%20of%20his%20kingdom%2C%20much%20of%20his%20rule.%20So%20in%20that%20sense%20I%20think%20he%20was%20a%20Buddhist.%20He%20remained%20a%20Buddhist%20because%20during%20this%20time%20he%20wrote%20two%20inscriptions%20that%20are%20specifically%20Buddhist.%20The%20Bairat%20inscription%20was%20written%20by%20this%20guy%20who%20was%20a%20king%20but%20he%20was%20a%20layman%20trying%20to%20tell%20Buddhist%20monks%20what%20to%20read.%20He%20was%20sending%20him%20them%20a%20reading%20list%20saying%20that%2C%20hey%20you%20want%20to%20read%20these%2C%20these%20are%20the%20important%20Buddhist.%20And%20then%20he%20intervenes%20in%20the%20schism%20edict%20about%20monks%20who%20are%20troublemakers%2C%20who%20cause%20dissension%2C%20and%20how%20they%20should%20be%20expelled.%20So%20yeah%2C%20he%20remained%20a%20Buddhist%2C%20and%20he%20tried%20to%20intervene%20in%20ways%20almost%20sort%20of%20high-handed%20for%20a%20king%20with%20regard%20to%20monks.%20But%20in%20his%20real%20inscriptions%2C%20his%20message%20to%20the%20people%2C%20Buddhism%20is%20in%20the%20background%2C%20not%20in%20the%20foreground.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJS%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20You%20use%20this%20categorisation%20of%20civil%20religion%20to%20talk%20about%20how%20he%20tried%20to%20bring%20this%20very%20large%20and%20very%20diverse%20population%20he%20was%20ruling%20over%20together%2C%20and%20through%20his%20morals%20philosophy%20as%20well.%20Could%20you%20talk%20a%20little%20bit%20about%20how%20he%20did%20that%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%20Yes%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20whether%20he%20did%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJS%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Sorry%2C%20how%20he%20%3Cem%3Eattempted%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20do%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20This%20is%20me%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%2C%20theorise%20how%20he%20may%20have%20done%20it%20and%20this%20is%20of%20course%20modern%20categories%2C%20right%3F%20From%20Russo%20to%20Bella%2C%20that%20we%20are%20dealing%20with%2C%20with%20this.%20But%20trying%20to%20find%20out%2C%20what%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20do%20by%20presenting%20this%20moral%20philosophy%2C%20this%20dharma%20philosophy.%20I%20was%20trying%20to%20see%20how%20he%20may%20have%20been%20trying%20to%20forge%20a%20certain%20identity%20for%20people%20who%20had%20no%20identity.%20This%20is%20a%20large%20country%20which%20had%20never%20been%20brought%20into%20a%20single%20unity%3B%20even%20under%20Ashoka%20there%20may%20have%20been%20large%20areas%20of%20India%20that%20were%20sort%20of%20left%20out%20on%20their%20own.%20So%20how%20did%20he%20do%20that%3F%20Why%20did%20he%20do%20that%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETwo%20or%20three%20things%20happened%20he%20tried%20to%20bring%E2%80%A6%20Ashoka%20was%20the%20first%20to%20write.%20As%20far%20as%20you%20know.%20So%20he%20brings%20the%20first%20public%20documents%20written%2C%20you%20can%20actually%20go%20and%20see%20there%20are%20talking%20stones%2C%20which%20had%20never%20existed%20before.%20What%20would%20that%20have%20done%20to%20people%20who%20encountered%20this%3F%20He%20wrote%20in%20a%20single%20language%2C%20he%20wrote%20in%20different%20scripts%20%E2%80%93%20script%20is%20not%20the%20same%20as%20language%20and%20often%20people%20confuse%20this%2C%C2%A0because%20today%20in%20India%20scripts%20are%20often%20connected%20to%20specific%20languages.%20But%20Sanskrit%20is%20written%20%E2%80%93%20when%20I%20did%20my%20edition%20of%20Manu%2C%20I%20was%20delving%20into%20nine%20scripts%20%E2%80%93%20the%20same%20text%2C%20same%20language%2C%20but%20in%20nine%20scripts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESo%20he%20used%20a%20language%20which%20we%20call%20Magadhi%2C%20which%20is%20the%20Prakrit%20that%20was%20probably%20the%20native%20tongue%20of%20people%20who%20lived%20in%20the%20Magada%20region.%20He%20writes%20that%20everywhere%20including%20Karnataka%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20Bengal%2C%20Nepal%20%E2%80%93%20so%20he%E2%80%99s%20bringing%20a%20certain%20uniformity.%20So%20you%20have%20a%20script%2C%20a%20language%2C%20and%20I%20think%20the%20third%20ingredient%20of%20this%20was%20a%20certain%20common%20identity%20of%20aspiration%2C%20life.%20What%20life%20means.%20How%20should%20we%20live%20our%20lives%3F%20What%20are%20our%20final%20goals%20as%20a%20human%20being%3F%20In%20Sanskrit%20we%20call%20it%20the%20a%3Cem%3Ertha.%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20goals%20we%20go%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAnd%20I%20think%20we%20can%20at%20least%20theorise%20it%20using%20Rousseau%E2%80%99s%20word%20as%20a%20modern%20kind%20of%20civil%20religion.%20In%20other%20words%20you%20can%20be%20a%20Buddhist%2C%20you%20can%20be%20a%20Jain%2C%20you%20can%20be%20a%20Brahman%20but%20still%20connect%20at%20this%20upper%20level%2C%20almost%20an%20umbrella%20level%20of%20ideology%20which%20is%20dharma%20for%20him.%20People%20don%E2%80%99t%20realise%20that%20today%2C%20we%20think%20dharma%20is%20so%20important%2C%20so%20central%20for%20the%20whole%20of%20India%2C%20that%20it%20was%20there%20from%20the%20very%20beginning.%20It%20was%20not.%20All%20these%20words%20have%20histories%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20understand%20the%20history%20of%20them.%20If%20you%20look%20at%20the%20early%20Vedic%20period%2C%20dharma%20starts%20with%20the%20Rigveda%2C%2068%20times%20there%2C%20but%20later%20on%20it%20becomes%20marginal.%20Then%20this%20marginality%20is%20ruptured%20with%20Buddhism%20and%20especially%20with%20Ashoka.%20In%20this%20small%20number%20of%203%2C000%20odd%20words%2C%20he%20uses%20dharma%20over%20100%C2%A0times.%20So%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20centrepiece%20of%20his%20thought.%20He%E2%80%99s%20not%20just%20repeating%20what%20everybody%20was%20saying.%20He%20was%20doing%20something%20new%20and%20that%20I%20think%2C%20at%20least%20we%20can%20think%20of%20as%2C%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20forge%20a%20common%20spiritual%20life%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20time%20in%20world%20history%20I%20think%20that%20the%20political%20authority%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20king%20here%20was%20trying%20to%20have%20a%20mass%20education%20campaign%2C%20educating%20the%20people%20in%20moral%20philosophy.%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20whole%20point%20of%20these%20letters%20that%20he%20wrote.%20They%E2%80%99re%20not%20edicts%20really.%20Everybody%20calls%20it%20an%20edict%20but%20these%20are%20letters.%20I%20often%20call%20them%20Ashoka%E2%80%99s%20writings%20rather%20than%20edicts%2C%20to%20make%20it%20a%20broader%20thing.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJS%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EYou%E2%80%99ve%20said%20in%20your%20book%20that%20the%20corpus%20of%20his%20writings%20available%20to%20us%20today%20are%20about%204%2C614%20words.%20Like%20you%20said%20these%20are%20words%20in%20which%20he%E2%80%99s%20asking%20the%20people%20to%20live%20in%20a%20certain%20way%20and%20also%20telling%20them%20about%20his%20philosophy%20and%20of%20course%20some%20are%20a%20little%20more%20administrative.%20You%20also%20said%20that%20some%20of%20these%20writings%20have%20literary%20merit%20and%20so%20we%20can%20call%20him%20a%20%E2%80%98writer%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EToday%20when%20we%20think%20of%20political%20leaders%20making%20speeches%20or%20writing%20in%20various%20forms%2C%20the%20assumption%20is%20that%20the%20ideology%20is%20theirs%20but%20the%20words%20are%20not%20theirs.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20speech%20writer%20or%20a%20publicist%20who%20is%20behind%20the%20precise%20words.%20What%20are%20the%20chances%20that%20these%20are%20in%20fact%20Ashoka%E2%80%99s%20words%20and%20should%20that%20impact%20how%20we%E2%80%99re%20reading%20them%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Yes%2C%20there%20is%20no%20way%20to%20tell%2C%20of%20course.%20You%20can%20argue%20both%20ways%20but%20the%20arguments%20for%20one%20or%20the%20other%20are%20equally%20weak.%20If%20you%20go%20to%20the%20parallels%20in%20the%20Roman%20Empire%20at%20the%20time%2C%20there%20was%20an%20epistolographer%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20called%2C%20a%20%E2%80%98writer%20of%20epistles%E2%80%99.%20Epistles%20are%20the%20official%20writings.%20So%20there%20may%20have%20been%20writers%20in%20the%20chancery%20of%20Ashoka%20who%20were%20responsible%20for%20diplomatic%20communications%2C%20etc%20that%20had%20to%20be%20done.%20Were%20they%20the%20people%20who%20actually%20wrote%20these%3F%20Personally%2C%20I%20think%20not%2C%20but%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20defend%20it.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20real%20proof%20to%20defend%20it.%20But%20when%20you%20read%C2%A0these%20as%20I%20have%20done%2C%20like%20every%20word%20and%20you%20get%20a%20certain%20feel%20for%20the%20writer%2C%20right%3F%20I%20assume%20you%20could%20do%20today%20with%20a%20computer%2C%20you%20know%20AI%20could%20be%20able%20to%20see%20whether%20it%20was%20written%20by%20this%20same%20person%2C%20right%3F%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20knowledge%20to%20do%20that%20but%20you%20get%20a%20certain%20feel%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EI%20think%20there%20is%20Ashoka%20behind%20those%20words.%20Even%20if%20not%20every%20word%20of%20that%20may%20have%20been%20written%20by%20him.%20They%20were%20certainly%20not%20written%20because%20ones%20in%20Gujarat%2C%20for%20example%2C%20they%20were%20semi-translations.%20So%20the%20word%20for%20example%20for%20a%20daughter%20in%20Magadhi%20is%20one%20thing%20and%20these%20people%20translate%20it%20into%20a%20much%20more%20Sanskritic%20thing%20over%20here.%20There%20are%20many%20examples%20of%20that%2C%20so%20clearly%20they%20were%20not%20his%20words.%20Somebody%20is%20translating%20now.%20Then%20it%20was%20translated%20into%20Aramaic%20and%20Greek%2C%20clearly%20they%20were%20the%20work%20of%20translators%2C%20right%3F%20But%20there%20is%20a%20personality%20behind%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20all%20we%20can%20say.%20In%20that%20sense%2C%20these%20are%20the%20words%20of%20Ashoka.%20Even%20today%E2%80%99s%20politicians%2C%20if%20they%20are%20good%20politicians%2C%20I%20think%20they%20would%20not%20parrot%20what%20somebody%20else%20has%20written%20but%20would%20want%20that%20person%20to%20say%20what%20he%20wants%20to%20say%2C%20perhaps%20in%20a%20better%20way%2C%20more%20eloquent%20way.%20Still%20they%20are%20his%20words.%20I%20think%20we%20can%20say%20these%20are%20Ashoka%E2%80%99s%20writings%20in%20that%20broad%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJS%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Going%20back%20to%20his%20attempt%20to%20build%20this%20unifying%20moral%20philosophy%2C%20you%20refer%20to%20his%20usage%20of%20the%20term%20%3Cem%3Epasanda%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20then%20how%20that%20changed%20going%2C%20and%20later%20became%20more%20derogatory.%20So%20what%20was%20his%20meaning%20of%20it%20and%20what%20did%20it%20mean%20for%20him%20to%20call%20himself%20a%20patron%20of%20all%20pasandas%3F%20What%20was%20the%20impact%20of%20that%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20So%20there%20are%20four%20parts%20of%20my%20book%2C%20and%20I%20try%20to%20think%20that%20each%20of%20parts%20as%20four%20aspects%20of%20what%20Ashoka%20was%2C%20his%20defining%20characteristics%2C%20and%20the%20last%20one%20is%20that%20he%E2%80%99s%20an%20ecumenist.%20The%20word%20didn%E2%80%99t%20exist%20at%20the%20time%2C%20again%20we%20are%20imposing%20a%20category%20from%20here.%20It%20means%20that%20he%20wanted%20people%20following%20different%20ideologies%20and%20religions%20etc%20to%20connect%20with%20each%20other%20and%2C%20at%20a%20minimum%2C%20be%20civil%20to%20each%20other%2C%20and%20at%20the%20best%2C%20as%20the%20ultimate%2C%20to%20learn%20from%20each%20other.%20The%20word%20he%20uses%2C%20%E2%80%98samavay%E2%80%99%20which%20comes%20from%20to%20come%20together%20in%20a%20gathering%2C%20meeting%20so%20that%20they%20can%20talk%20to%20each%20other%20and%20learn%20from%20each%20other.%20He%20says%20you%20cannot%2C%20he%20uses%20the%20word%20in%20Sanskrit%20%3Cem%3Eshruta%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20hearing%2C%20right%3F%20It%20is%20found%20in%20Hindi%20and%20every%20modern%20Indian%20language%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Ebahushruta%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20Sanskrit%20means%20%E2%80%98much%20heard%E2%80%99%2C%20it%20means%20one%20who%20has%20heard%20a%20lot.%20In%20English%20we%20would%20have%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98read%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20well-read%20man.%20A%20well-read%20man%20cannot%20be%20well%20read%20unless%20he%20reads%20a%20lot.%20A%20much%20heard%20man%20cannot%20be%20much%20heard%20unless%20he%20listens%20to%20other%20people.%20That%E2%80%99s%20what%20he%E2%80%99s%20getting%20at%2C%20I%20think.%20This%20is%20where%20he%E2%80%99s%20much%20ahead%20of%20his%20time%2C%20I%20think.%20If%20you%20read%20around%20the%20writings%20of%20various%20religions%2C%20both%20Brahmanical%20and%20Buddhist%20and%20I%20give%20a%20couple%20of%20examples%20there%2C%20they%E2%80%99re%20calling%20each%20other%20names%2C%20right%3F%20Buddhists%20are%20comparing%20dogs%20favourably%20to%20Brahmins%2C%20right%3F%20Dogs%20are%20better%20than%C2%A0Brahmins%2C%20and%20the%20Brahmins%20likewise%20give%20back%20the%20same%20way%2C%20so%20yes%20I%20think%20he%20was%20trying%20to%20do%20something%20at%20which%20he%20probably%20failed.%20The%20failures%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20understand%2C%20but%20clearly%20if%20there%20was%20religious%20harmony%20during%20his%20time%2C%20if%20he%20was%20able%20to%20bring%20them%20together%2C%20it%20did%20not%20last%20too%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJS%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Unfortunately%20we%E2%80%99re%20running%20out%20of%20time%2C%20but%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20last%20question%20I%E2%80%99d%20like%20to%20pose%20to%20both%20of%20you.%20You%20say%20at%20some%20point%20in%20your%20book%20that%20the%20reimagination%20of%20the%20past%20to%20fit%20the%20needs%20of%20the%20present%20is%20inherently%20human.%20So%20what%20does%20that%20mean%20for%20how%20Ashoka%20is%20remembered%20and%20spoken%20of%20today%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Okay%2C%20this%20is%20rather%20difficult%20for%20me%20to%20do%20because%20unlike%20Ram%2C%20I%20am%20so%20much%20in%20the%20past%20that%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20do%20that%20much%20in%20the%20present.%20But%20I%20will%20give%20a%20talk%20at%20Ashoka%20University%2C%20their%20patron%20saint%20is%20Ashoka%20after%20all%2C%20to%20bring%20liberal%20arts%20education%20and%20Ashoka%E2%80%99s%20work%20with%20pasandas%20into%20dialogue%2C%20to%20say%20that%20liberal%20arts%20education%2C%20ultimately%2C%20is%20where%20you%20listen%20to%20others%2C%20you%20listen%20to%20a%20wide%20spectrum%20of%20intellectual%20pursuits%2C%20a%20wide%20spectrum%20of%20ideas%2C%20respecting%20everything%20but%20not%20accepting%20everything%2C%20right%3F%20But%20able%2C%20therefore%2C%20to%20interrogate%20this%20but%20become%20better%20persons%2C%20better%20scholars%2C%20better%20citizens%20who%20are%20able%20to%20go%20beyond%20themselves%20and%20their%20own%20little%20world.%20This%20little%20world%20is%20a%20pasanda%2C%20right%3F%20The%20larger%20world%20is%20the%C2%A0inter-pasanda%20under%20dialogue.%20And%20the%20little%20worlds%20we%20can%20think%20about%2C%20we%20come%20from%20our%20family%2C%20our%20group%2C%20our%20socio-economic%20group.%20In%20India%20it%20could%20be%20our%20caste%2C%20it%20could%20be%20many%20other%20small%20groups%2C%20but%20the%20ability%20to%20then%20transcend%20that%2C%20to%20penetrate%20those%20walls%20and%20see%20the%20others.%20I%20think%20that%20is%20a%20lasting%20legacy%20of%20Ashoka%20as%20we%20read%20his%20own%20writings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%20So%20I%E2%80%99d%20say%20that%20I%20always%20hesitate%20about%20what%20lessons%20one%20can%20draw%20from%20the%20past.%20Even%20though%20in%20my%20own%20work%2C%20I%20mean%20there%20are%20two%20sides%20%E2%80%93%20I%20write%20scholarly%20books%20about%20the%20past%20and%20I%20write%20polemical%20interventions%20of%20the%20present%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99d%20like%20them%20to%20be%20separate.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20I%20think%20the%20great%20value%20of%20Patrick%E2%80%99s%20book%20is%20that%20it%20shows%20you%20another%20world%20and%20it%20brings%20you%20into%20the%20world%20of%20ancient%20India%2C%20their%20debates%2C%20their%20arguments%2C%20their%20lifestyles%2C%20their%20anxieties%2C%20through%20this%20very%20special%20figure.%20In%20that%20sense%2C%20history%20is%20a%20broader%20form%20of%20education%20without%20any%20immediate%20lessons%20on%20how%20to%20conduct%20your%20life%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ENow%20just%20listening%20to%20Patrick%2C%20I%20deviate%20very%20little%20because%20it%20is%20so%20fascinating%20listening%20to%20him.%20One%20thing%20that%20struck%20me%20while%20reading%20Patrick%E2%80%99s%20book%20is%20that%20Nehru%20actually%20references%20Ashoka%20and%20admired%20Ashoka%2C%20including%20in%20the%20symbol%20and%20all%20of%20that.%20But%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20virtually%20reference%20in%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20writings.%20But%20when%20I%20read%20Patrick%E2%80%99s%20book%20and%20his%20analysis%2C%20when%20he%20says%20that%20Ashoka%20is%20the%20only%20king%20who%20said%20sorry%20%E2%80%93%20Gandhi%20may%20be%20the%20only%20politician%20who%20said%20I%20have%20made%20a%20Himalayan%20blunder.%20Or%20if%20you%20look%20at%20ecumenism%20and%20relations%20between%20your%20faith%20and%20other%20faith%20or%20if%20you%20look%20at%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20much%20more%20expansive%20view%20of%20dharma%20there%20is%20there%20in%20the%20narrow%20Brahmanical%20tradition%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20intriguing.%20I%20just%20wonder%2C%20you%C2%A0know%2C%20that%20maybe%20Gandhi%20takes%20something%20from%20Ashoka%20without%20acknowledging%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Yes%2C%20did%20he%20read%20Ashoka%20during%20that%20time%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERG%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Nehru%20did.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPO%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Of%20course%2C%20but%20Gandhi%20didn%E2%80%99t%20didn%E2%80%99t%20tap%20on%20to%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EJS%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Interesting.%20Thank%20you%20both%20so%20much%20for%20joining%20us%20today.%20This%20was%20great%2C%20thank%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696764635000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F07161408%2Fashoka-collage.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Ffull-text-ashoka-was-strong-enough-to-say-he-was-sorry-about-things-hed-done%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Patrick%20Oliv