B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20Syrian%20foreign%20ministry%20backed%20the%20Hamas%20attacks%2C%20calling%20it%20an%20%26quot%3Bhonourable%20achievement%26quot%3B%20and%20expressing%20%26quot%3Bsupport%26quot%3B%20for%20forces%20%26quot%3Bfighting%20against%20Zionist%20terrorism%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETehran%2C%20known%20to%20back%20Hamas%2C%20had%20a%20similar%20response.%20A%20senior%20adviser%20to%20Iran's%20supreme%20leader%20Ayatollah%20Ali%20Khamenei%20called%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bproud%20operation%26quot%3B%2C%20news%20agency%20AFP%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EQatar%20called%20upon%20all%20sides%20to%20de-escalate%20while%20holding%20Israel%20%26quot%3Bsolely%20responsible%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20ongoing%20escalation.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20West%20Stands%20With%20Israel%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20expressed%20solidarity%20with%20Israel%2C%20its%20long-time%20ally.%20Soon%20after%20the%20attacks%2C%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20expressed%20condolences%20for%20the%20deaths%20caused%20by%20the%20Hamas%20offensive.%20He%20later%20stressed%20that%20his%20administration%20support%20for%20Israel%20is%20%26quot%3Brock%20solid%20and%20unwavering%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20several%20decades%2C%20the%20US%20has%20mediated%20steps%20to%20normalise%20relations%20between%20Israel%20and%20other%20countries%20in%20the%20West%20Asian%20region.%20It%20was%20with%20Washington's%20support%20that%20the%20Abraham%20Accords%20agreements%20were%20signed%20between%20Israel%2C%20UAE%2C%20Sudan%2C%20Morocco%20and%20Bahrain%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fi8f2vspo_netanyahu_625x300_27_September_23.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20West%20Asian%20region%20is%20critical%20to%20the%20US%20scheme%20of%20things%20for%20reasons%20ranging%20from%20cultural%20to%20strategic.%20This%20focus%20has%20been%20reflected%20in%20policies%20of%20the%20US%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Donald%20Trump%20administration%20had%20slashed%20aid%20to%20Palestinians%2C%20the%20Biden%20regime%20restored%20some%20of%20this%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EUK%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak%20called%20the%20Hamas%20attack%20%26quot%3Bcowardly%20and%20depraved%26quot%3B%20and%20expressed%20full%20solidarity%20to%20Netanyahu.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20European%20Union%20condemned%20the%20Hamas%20attack%2C%20with%20European%20Commission%20President%20Ursula%20von%20der%20Leyen%20calling%20the%20attack%20%26quot%3Bterrorism%20in%20its%20most%20despicable%20form%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFrance%20joined%20others%20in%20the%20West%20in%20condemning%20the%20attacks.%20France%20stands%20in%20solidarity%20with%20Israel%20and%20the%20Israelis%2C%20committed%20to%20their%20security%20and%20their%20right%20to%20defend%20themselves%2C%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20posted%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20India%2C%20China%20And%20Pakistan%20Said%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESoon%20after%20yesterday's%20attacks%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20posted%20on%20X%20that%20he%20is%20%26quot%3Bdeeply%20shocked%20by%20the%20news%20of%20terrorist%20attacks%20in%20Israel%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BWe%20stand%20in%20solidarity%20with%20Israel%20at%20this%20difficult%20hour%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20India's%20relations%20with%20Israel%20have%20seen%20multiple%20stages.%20Right%20after%20Independence%20in%201947%2C%20India%20had%20been%20cautious%20in%20recognising%20the%20Israel%20State%2C%20primarily%20because%20of%20New%20Delhi's%20relations%20with%20Arab%20countries.%20In%201950%2C%20it%20formally%20recognised%20Israel%20as%20a%20state%2C%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20saying%20%26quot%3BIsrael%20is%20a%20fact%26quot%3B.%20An%20Indian%20embassy%20in%20Israel%2C%20however%2C%20was%20set%20up%20only%20in%201992.%20On%20the%20Israel-Palestinian%20conflict%2C%20India%20maintained%20a%20neutral%20position%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20articulating%20the%20Indian%20position%20on%20the%20issue%2C%20then%20External%20Affairs%20Minister%20Sushma%20Swaraj%20had%20said%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20absolutely%20no%20change%20in%20India's%20policy%20towards%20Palestine%2C%20which%20is%20that%20we%20fully%20support%20the%20Palestinian%20cause%20while%20maintaining%20good%20relations%20with%20Israel%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%20%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2018-01%2Fbenjamin-netanyahu-and-narendra-modi_650x400_71516023168.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia-Israel%20relations%20have%20seen%20immense%20growth%20during%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government's%20regime.%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20was%20the%20first%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20to%20visit%20Israel%20in%202017%2C%20a%20year%20which%20also%20saw%20India%20become%20Tel%20Aviv's%20largest%20arms%20customer.%20In%202019%2C%20India%20also%20voted%20in%20favour%20of%20Israel's%20resolution%20to%20deny%20observer%20status%20to%20Palestinian%20non-governmental%20organisation%20Shahed%20at%20the%20UN%20Economic%20and%20Social%20Council.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20said%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bdeeply%20concerned%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20%26quot%3Bescalation%20of%20tension%20and%20violence%26quot%3B%20between%20Israel%20and%20Palestine.%20Beijing%20said%20%26quot%3Bthe%20repeated%20clashes%20between%20Palestine%20and%20Israel%20fully%20demonstrate%20that%20the%20long-term%20stagnation%20of%20the%20peace%20process%20is%20unsustainable%26quot%3B%2C%20news%20agency%20AFP%20reported.%20%26quot%3BThe%20fundamental%20way%20out%20of%20the%20Palestinian-Israeli%20conflict%20l