0Soviet-era%20boxers.%3Cp%3EStella%20Kalinina%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAkimova%20never%20wanted%20to%20leave%20Ukraine%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20only%2018%20months%20ago%20when%20Akimova%2C%2033%2C%20thought%20her%20days%20were%20numbered%2C%20first%20because%20of%20the%20war%20and%20later%2C%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20paralyzing%20limbo%20of%20losing%20her%20sense%20of%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Russia's%20invasion%20in%20early%202022%2C%20and%20during%20her%20first%20months%20in%20the%20US%2C%20Akimova%20said%2C%20she%20hated%20that%20Americans%20could%20keep%20a%20positive%20outlook%20on%20life%20while%20she%20stayed%20up%20late%2C%20sending%20WhatsApp%20messages%20to%20relatives%20in%20Odesa%20and%20Kyiv%2C%20trying%20to%20start%20her%20new%20life%20after%20resettling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20missed%20the%20mundane%20in%20Odesa%2C%20even%20how%20the%20acrid%20smell%20of%20her%20neighbors%20frying%20tinned%20goby%20fish%20would%20waft%20through%20the%20calm%20seaside%20air%20and%20into%20her%20home%2C%20uninvited.%20She%20missed%20the%20rigor%20of%20her%20daily%20Karate%20practice%20and%20often%20thought%20about%20her%20and%20her%2012-year-old%20daughter%2C%20Arina's%2C%20karate%20coach%2C%20who%20once%20told%20her%20the%20only%20time%20it%20was%20OK%20to%20miss%20a%20workout%20was%20when%20you%20die.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20felt%20close%20enough%20to%20that%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20how%20excited%20her%20daughter%20was%20about%20Disneyland%20and%20life%20in%20the%20US%2C%20depression%20ate%20away%20at%20Akimova.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20five%20months%20into%20her%20time%20in%20the%20US%2C%20she%20met%20someone%20who%20reinvigorated%20that%20sense%20of%20adrenalized%20regiment%20and%20purpose%20into%20her%20life.%20Without%20much%20to%20do%2C%20and%20too%20much%20time%20to%20doomscroll%2C%20Akimova%20followed%20an%20algorithmic%20thread%20on%20Instagram%20that%20led%20her%20to%20the%20page%20of%20a%20boxing%20gym%20that%20was%20set%20to%20open%20in%20Toluca%20Lake%2C%20near%20North%20Hollywood%2C%20where%20she%20resettled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20where%20she%20met%20her%20boxing%20trainer%2C%20Salman%20Poddubnov%2C%2035%2C%20a%20man%20who%20came%20from%20%E2%80%94%20who%20escaped%20%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20country%20that%20invaded%20her%20homeland.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20January%202023%2C%20Akimova%20joined%20his%20gym%20and%20felt%20born%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20like%20being%20underwater%20for%20a%20long%20time%2C%20and%20then%20coming%20up%20for%20air%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20remembered%20telling%20her%20sister%2C%20still%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20over%20a%20late-night%20phone%20call%20through%20which%20air%20sirens%20could%20be%20heard%20in%20the%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAt%20the%20outset%20of%20the%20war%2C%20Akimova%20sought%20refuge%20in%20an%20underground%20parking%20garage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAkimova's%20sing-songy%20voice%20shifts%20from%20a%20bubbly%20tone%20to%20exasperation%20in%20seconds%20as%20she%20reflects%20on%20her%20journey%20from%20a%20war%20that%20has%20raged%20in%20some%20form%20since%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETen%20days%20into%20Russia's%20full-scale%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20Akimova%20found%20herself%20and%20her%20daughter%20sheltering%20from%20warplanes%20in%20the%20underground%20parking%20garage%20of%20their%20apartment%20building%20in%20Odesa%2C%20she%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20sick%20with%20a%20cold%2C%20and%20her%20fridge%20was%20empty.%20Within%2024%20hours%2C%20grocery%20stores%20in%20her%20city%20were%20out%20of%20food%2C%20and%20the%20pharmacies%2C%20which%20she%20hadn't%20had%20time%20to%20pass%20by%20in%20the%20days%20before%20the%20invasion%2C%20were%20out%20of%20medicine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20worried%2C%20too%2C%20that%20her%20daughter%20would%20get%20pneumonia%20sleeping%20on%20the%20frigid%20concrete%20where%20cars%20parked%2C%20with%20just%20a%20few%20blankets%20to%20keep%20her%20warm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20idyllic%20lifestyle%20%E2%80%94%20working%20as%20a%20teacher%2C%20later%20designing%20floral%20arrangements%2C%20and%20finally%20as%20a%20makeup%20artist%20%E2%80%94%20faded%20away%2C%20and%20she%20decided%20to%20create%20the%20safest%20possible%20life%20for%20herself%20and%20her%20daughter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20trudged%205%20miles%20by%20foot%20from%20a%20border%20crossing%20backed%20up%20with%20cars%20to%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20Moldovan%20border%2C%20where%20they%20were%20met%20by%20some%20of%20her%20karate%20teammates%20from%20Ukraine%2C%20who%20helped%20them%20get%20tickets%20aboard%20a%20rickety%20train%20to%20Romania.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20train%20was%20repurposed%20to%20help%20resettle%20migrants%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20full-scale%20invasion.%20Its%20roof%20was%20riddled%20with%20holes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20first%20time%20they%20could%20fall%20asleep%20%E2%80%94%20on%20each%20other's%20shoulders%2C%20with%20no%20fear%20of%20bombardment%20%E2%80%94%20in%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Romania%2C%20Akimova%20and%20her%20daughter%20waited%20for%20half%20a%20day%20until%20a%20Czech%20relative%20arrived%20and%20invited%20them%20to%20live%20with%20them%20in%20Prague%20for%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20Akimova%20and%20her%20daughter%20took%20the%20leap%20and%20decided%20to%20try%20to%20gain%20entry%20into%20the%20US%20and%20join%20Akimova's%20partner%2C%20a%20Ukrainian%20who%20lives%20in%20Los%20Angeles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20flew%20to%20Mexico%2C%20where%20they%20first%20tried%20to%20cross%20the%20border%20at%20Tijuana%2C%20but%20turned%20away%20when%20they%20saw%20the%20crowds%20at%20the%20crossing.%20They%20were%20later%20driven%20by%20Ukrainian%20volunteers%20to%20the%20Mexicali-Calexico%20border%2C%20where%2C%20after%20four%20hours%2C%20they%20were%20granted%20humanitarian%20parole%20in%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20journey%20was%20arduous%2C%20and%20the%20following%20months%20weighed%20heavily%20on%20Akimova%20as%20she%20tried%20to%20make%20sense%20of%20her%20new%20immigration%20status%20and%20navigate%20with%20minimal%20English%20skills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20enlisting%20in%20ESL%20classes%20and%20registering%20her%20daughter%20in%20a%20public%20school%2C%20her%20day-to-day%20life%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20felt%20more%20stable.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20she%20ached%20for%20her%20homeland.%20Her%20attempts%20to%20make%20tvarog%2C%20a%20pillowy%20fermented%20farmer's%20cheese%20popular%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20didn't%20help.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBegrudgingly%20picking%20up%20ingredients%20from%20a%20Russian%20store%2C%20she%20mixed%20the%20warmed%20milk%20with%20vinegar%20as%20she%20always%20had%2C%20watching%20the%20whey%20separate%20and%20the%20cheese%20curdle.%20But%20when%20she%20strained%20the%20fluffy%20mixture%20with%20cheesecloth%20and%20added%20buttermilk%2C%20something%20was%20off%20%E2%80%94%20either%20the%20American%20buttermilk%20or%20the%20absence%20of%20Odesa's%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20wasn't%20until%20she%20set%20foot%20in%20Poddubnov's%20gym%20that%20she%20felt%20at%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20my%20country%20when%20I%20practiced%20karate%2C%20I%20was%20really%20organized%3A%20If%20you%20have%20a%20problem%2C%20you%20should%20go%20work%20out%3B%20if%20you're%20happy%2C%20you%20should%20go%20work%20out%3B%20if%20you%20need%20to%20solve%20a%20problem%2C%20you%20should%20work%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Akimova%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20like%20medicine%20for%20everything.%20And%20here%2C%20it's%20the%20same.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20wearing%20mouth%20guard%20and%20boxing%20gloves.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651da1512ce014759e74ca5d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnzelika%20Akimova%20said%20the%20routine%20she%20found%20at%20the%20Eastern%20Block%20Boxing%20gym%20helped%20her%20adjust%20to%20life%20in%20the%20US.%3Cp%3EStella%20Kalinina%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELike%20many%20Ukrainians%2C%20Akimova%20has%20fought%20for%20her%20place%20in%20the%20US%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAkimova%20is%20one%20of%20the%20more%20than%20270%2C000%20Ukrainians%20who%20have%20arrived%20in%20the%20US%20since%20Russia%20invaded%20Ukraine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20least%2025%2C000%20of%20them%20entered%20the%20US%20through%20the%20southern%20border%20in%202022%2C%20before%20the%20US%20government%20established%20the%20Uniting%20for%20Ukraine%20program%20in%20April%20of%20that%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20nonprofit%20Lutheran%20Immigration%20and%20Refugee%20Service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20bulk%20of%20new%20Ukrainians%20%E2%80%94%20at%20least%20146%2C000%20fleeing%20the%20war%20%E2%80%94%20have%20been%20resettled%20through%20the%20parole%20program%2C%20according%20to%20LIRS.%20The%20sponsorship%20program%20allows%20Ukrainians%20to%20live%20in%20the%20US%20for%20two%20years%20on%20a%20faster%20track%20to%20citizenship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%201.7%20million%20Americans%20have%20applied%20to%20be%20sponsors%2C%20LIRS%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKrish%20O'Mara%20Vignarajah%2C%20the%20president%20of%20LIRS%2C%20told%20Insider%20that%20parole%20status%20did%20not%20necessarily%20create%20a%20clear%20path%20to%20be%20granted%20asylum%20and%20later%20permanent%20residency.%20So%20in%20August%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dhs.gov%2Fnews%2F2023%2F08%2F18%2Fsecretary-mayorkas-extends-and-redesignates-temporary-protected-status-ukraine%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20extended%3C%2Fa%3E%20Temporary%20Protected%20Status%20for%20Ukrainians%20until%20April%202025%2C%20providing%20more%20options%20for%20Ukrainians%20to%20try%20to%20extend%20their%20refuge%20in%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202022%2C%20Akimova%20and%20Arina%20were%20granted%20TPS%2C%20which%20made%20their%20place%20in%20the%20US%20slightly%20more%20rooted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20are%20still%20uniting%20factors%20making%20life%20in%20the%20US%20difficult%20for%20many%20new%20Ukrainians%20like%20Akimova%2C%20regardless%20of%20immigration%20status.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%2C%20Akimova%20and%20Arina%20arrived%20at%20a%20time%20when%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2022%2F05%2F11%2Fcpi-april-2022.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehistoric%208.3%25%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%20caused%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20in%20the%20US%20to%20skyrocket%2C%20especially%20compared%20to%20the%20cost%20of%20living%20in%20Ukraine.%20And%20many%20parolees%20that%20arrived%20are%20women%20and%20children%2C%20according%20to%20LIRS%2C%20creating%20issues%20in%20terms%20of%20securing%20childcare%20and%20employment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20weekly%20basis%2C%20Akimova%20has%20been%20working%20against%20the%20clock%20with%20her%20immigration%20lawyer%2C%20trying%20to%20secure%20an%20extension%20to%20her%20and%20Arina's%20TPS%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20general%2C%20we've%20seen%20the%20Ukrainians%20we%20serve%20struggle%20with%20the%20uncertainty%20of%20what%20will%20happen%20after%20parole%20and%20whether%20they%20will%20be%20approved%20for%20another%20status%20like%20TPS%20or%20asylum%2C%26quot%3B%20Vignarajah%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BUkrainians%20are%20also%20experiencing%20the%20trauma%20of%20losing%20their%20homes%20and%20being%20separated%20from%20family%20and%20loved%20ones.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIncreasingly%2C%20Akimova's%20future%20here%20is%20materializing%20after%20a%20relative%20shipped%20Akimova's%20master's%20degree%20to%20her%20home%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20%E2%80%94%20which%20allowed%20her%20to%20begin%20community%20college%20classes%20in%20English%20and%20art%20in%20the%20late%20summer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Woman%20and%20man%20standing%20next%20to%20each%20other%20in%20doorway.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651da20442ecf94db477e5d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAnzelika%20Akimova%20(left)%20formed%20a%20unique%20bond%20with%20her%20Russian%20boxing%20trainer%2C%20Salman%20Poddubnov%20(right).%3Cp%3EStella%20Kalinina%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoddubnov%20was%20a%20target%20of%20Russia's%20government%20too%2C%20in%20a%20different%20way%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20gym%2C%20too%2C%20has%20been%20Poddubnov's%20place%20of%20refuge.%20It's%20marked%20with%20the%20slogan%20%26quot%3Bno%20nationality%2C%20no%20skin%20color%2C%20no%20politics%3A%20only%20boxing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20cuts%20a%20stoic%20and%20alert%20figure%20in%20the%20gym%2C%20in%20one%20breath%20shouting%20instructions%2C%20cracking%20a%20joke%20in%20the%20next%2C%20over%20a%20rotating%20soundtrack%20of%20Russian%20tech%20house%20or%20American%20gangster%20rap.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20their%20paths%20aligned%20at%20Eastern%20Block%20Boxing%2C%20Poddubnov%20fought%20as%20an%20amateur%20boxer%20in%20Russia.%20He%20later%20entered%20local%20politics%2C%20getting%20a%20job%20as%20a%20vice%20mayor%20in%20the%20industrial%20Russian%20city%20of%20Volzhsky%2C%20a%20dozen%20miles%20from%20the%20famed%20World%20War%20II%20Battle%20of%20Stalingrad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20life%20was%20pretty%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20Poddubnov%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIf%20it%20wasn't%20for%20politics%2C%20maybe%20I'd%20still%20be%20there.%20In%20Russia%2C%20if%20you%20don't%20agree%20with%20something%2C%20you%20will%20go%20to%20jail%3B%20you%20have%20a%20choice%3A%20jail%20or%20USA.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPoddubnov%20told%20Insider%20he%20was%20run%20out%20as%20Volzhsky's%20vice%20mayor%20in%202016%2C%20after%20that%20year's%20legislative%20and%20state%20elections%2C%20as%20Vladimir%20Putin's%20allies%20took%20over%20the%20region's%20governorship%20and%20brought%20a%20corruption%20case%20against%20him%20and%20local%20mayors%2C%20clearing%20house%20and%20ensuring%20that%20allies%20took%20their%20spots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20year%2C%20what%20he%20felt%20was%20a%20phony%20corruption%20case%20against%20him%20was%20heating%20up%2C%20Poddubnov%20would%20kiss%20his%20young%20daughter%20one%20last%20time%20late%20at%20night%20and%20take%20a%20flight%20to%20the%20US%20with%20%243%2C000%20and%20hopes%20of%20reviving%20his%20boxing%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20soon%20after%20arriving%20in%20the%20US%2C%20he%20mixed%20with%20the%20wrong%20crowd%2C%20he%20told%20Insider%2C%20and%20served%20close%20to%20two%20years%20across%20six%20federal%20prisons%20after%20he%20became%20a%20driver%20involved%20in%20a%2025-person%20money-laundering%20ring%20run%20by%20Eastern%20Europeans%20across%20the%20US%2C%20according%20to%20court%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20in%20the%20prison%20system%2C%20Poddubnov%20trained%20groups%20of%20men%20and%20was%20encouraged%20by%20fellow%20prisoners%20to%20open%20his%20own%20gym%20after%20his%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%20of%20last%20year%2C%20after%20over%20a%20year%20of%20freedom%20and%20training%20clients%20in%20his%20backyard%2C%20Poddubnov%20opened%20Eastern%20Block%20Boxing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Soviet%20style%20is%20characterized%20by%20long-distance%20jabs%20and%20straight%20right%20hands%2C%20hooks%20with%20palms%20facing%20down%2C%20a%20pendulum%20step%2C%20and%20shifty%20angular%20footwork.%20It%20was%20popularized%20by%20the%20height%20of%20the%20cold%20war%20and%20shared%20by%20former%20members%20of%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20is%20still%20used%20by%20Ukrainian%20and%20Russian%20fighters%2C%20as%20well%20as%20fighters%20from%20other%20former%20Soviet%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBeautiful%2C%26quot%3B%20Poddubnov%20says%20to%20Akimova%20during%20their%20training%20one%20balmy%20summer%20morning.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20Soviet%20Union%20boxing%2C%20keeping%20your%20distance.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Man%20wearing%20boxing%20gloves%20leaning%20over%20a%20boxing%20ring.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651da097617692f0d03f159b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESalman%20Poddubnov%20opened%20the%20boxing%20gym%20after%20a%20stint%20in%20prison%2C%20where%20he%20trained%20fellow%20inmates.%20Now%2C%20his%20gym%20is%20a%20place%20for%20Eastern%20Europeans%20to%20find%20common%20ground.%3Cp%3EStella%20Kalinina%20for%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EEach%20day%2C%20they%20keep%20space%20to%20talk%20about%20the%20realities%20of%20the%20war%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMultiple%20times%20a%20week%2C%20Akimova%20tells%20Poddubnov%20what%20is%20going%20on%20with%20her%20community%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20they%20lament%20how%20close%20many%20Russians%20and%20Ukrainians%20were%20before%20the%20war.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20her%20Instagram%2C%20Akimova%20routinely%20speaks%20out%20against%20the%20war%2C%20calling%20Russia%20a%20%26quot%3Bterrorist%20state%26quot%3B%20for%20its%20actions.%20Poddubnov%20agrees%20with%20the%20political%20assessment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20very%20good%20that%20we%20live%20here%2C%20on%20the%20other%20side%2C%26quot%3B%20Poddubnov%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BHere%20you%20see%20it%20like%20a%20tennis%20match%2C%20and%20you%20can%20understand%20what%20is%20going%20on.%20In%20Russia%2C%20people%20don't%20see%20this%2C%20they%20see%20the%20'special%20military%20operation.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPoddubnov%20doesn't%20plan%20to%20go%20back%20to%20Russia%20any%20time%20soon%2C%20in%20part%20be