%20to%20loneliness%2C%20young%20people%20are%20particularly%20at%20risk.%20The%20rate%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-z-blame-loneliness-on-housing-affordability-crisis-2023-4%5C%22%3Eloneliness%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20US%20young%20adults%20has%20increased%20every%20year%20between%201976%20and%202019%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hhs.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fsurgeon-general-social-connection-advisory.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20the%20pandemic%20only%20made%20things%20worse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%202009%20and%202019%2C%20the%20share%20of%20high-school%20students%20reporting%20%26quot%3Bpersistent%20feelings%20of%20sadness%20or%20hopelessness%26quot%3B%20increased%20by%2040%25%2C%20according%20to%20a%202021%20Surgeon%20General's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hhs.gov%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fsurgeon-general-youth-mental-health-advisory.pdf%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Data%20on%20grade-school-aged%20children%20is%20limited%20in%20the%20US%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ons.gov.uk%2Fpeoplepopulationandcommunity%2Fwellbeing%2Farticles%2Fchildrensandyoungpeoplesexperiencesofloneliness%2F2018%23%3A~%3Atext%3D11.3%2525%2520of%2520children%2520said%2520that%2Cof%2520those%2520who%2520did%2520not.%5C%22%3Eresearch%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20other%20countries%20has%20found%20that%20young%20children%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F28892142%2F%5C%22%3Earen't%20immune%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20these%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221766%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22girls%20basketball%20team%20sad%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64f210a59b265c001993bd8b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221325%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EKids%20who%20participated%20in%20individual%20sports%20like%20tennis%20or%20gymnastics%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20face%20mental-health%20challenges%20than%20team%20sports%20participants%20and%20kids%20who%20played%20no%20sports%20at%20all.%3Cp%3EJohn%20Ewing%2FPortland%20Press%20Herald%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rise%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-z-blame-loneliness-on-housing-affordability-crisis-2023-4%5C%22%3Esocial%20media%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20popular%20explanation%20for%20the%20uptick%20in%20loneliness.%20But%20when%20young%20people%20spend%20more%20time%20on%20their%20phones%2C%20they're%20also%20spending%20less%20time%20on%20other%20activities%20%E2%80%94%20like%20sports%20%E2%80%94%20that%20could%20benefit%20their%20mental%20health.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%2037%25%20of%20US%20children%20between%20the%20ages%20of%206%20and%2012%20regularly%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprojectplay.org%2Fstate-of-play-2022%2Fparticipation-trends%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplayed%20a%20team%20sport%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Sports%20and%20Fitness%20Industry%20Association%2C%20down%20from%2045%25%20in%202008.%20During%20the%202018-2019%20school%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-school-sports-participation-declines-2019-8%5C%22%3Ehigh-school%20sports%20participation%3C%2Fa%3E%20declined%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%2030%20years%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Federation%20of%20State%20High%20School%20Associations.%20After%20two%20years%20with%20insufficient%20data%20due%20to%20the%20pandemic%2C%20participation%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nfhs.org%2Fmedia%2F5989280%2F2021-22_participation_survey.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeclined%20again%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202021-2022.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FJ61yg%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Youth%20team%20sports%20participation%20rates%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%3ETeam%20sports%20make%20kids%20less%20lonely%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20ask%20many%20US%20parents%2C%20not%20playing%20a%20sport%20could%20hinder%20their%20child's%20social%20development.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFifty-eight%20percent%20of%20US%20adults%20think%20that%20participating%20in%20organized%20sports%20makes%20children%20less%20lonely%2C%20a%20YouGov%20survey%20of%202%2C000%20US%20adults%20conducted%20in%20July%20and%20August%20in%20partnership%20with%20Insider%20found%3B%2089%25%20of%20respondents%20agreed%20that%20organized%20sports%20%26quot%3Bprovide%20opportunities%20for%20children%20to%20make%20friends.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FvHN6V%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Share%20who%20somewhat%20or%20strongly%20agree%20about%20the%20following%20regarding%20organized%20youth%20sports%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22442%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20few%20studies%20to%20explore%20sports%20participation's%20connection%20to%20youth%20loneliness%20was%20conducted%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC9874288%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEuropean%20researchers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202019.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20essential%20finding%20is%20that%20sports%20participation%20in%20childhood%20can%20protect%20against%20loneliness%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%20%26quot%3BBy%20virtue%20of%20sports%20activity%2C%20which%20provides%20children%20to%20meet%20their%20social%20needs%20and%20expectations%2C%20sports-active%20children%20are%20less%20lonely.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexercise-makes-you-happier-than-money-says-yale-and-oxford-study-2019-4%5C%22%3Ewide%20body%20of%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20suggests%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-sports-can-change-your-lifespan-2016-11%5C%22%3Ephysical%20and%20social%20benefits%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20sports%20participation%20could%20be%20contributing%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexercise-is-good-for-our-mental-health-but-more-is-not-always-better-2018-8%5C%22%3Eworse%20mental-health%20outcomes%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20young%20Americans.%20In%202022%2C%20a%20national%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.fullerton.edu%2F2022%2F06%2Fnational-study-finds-youth-participation-in-team-sports-linked-to-fewer-mental-health-difficulties%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20over%2011%2C000%20young%20people%20found%20that%20children%20who%20participated%20in%20organized%20team%20sports%20were%20at%20a%20lower%20risk%20of%20experiencing%20mental-health%20challenges%20than%20children%20who%20played%20no%20sports%20at%20all.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224608%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Athletics%20Royals%20Baseball%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651b1eb1617692f0d03ce882%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223456%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20young%20Kansas%20City%20Royals%20fan%20watches%20batting%20practice%20before%20a%20baseball%20game%20against%20the%20Oakland%20Athletics%20Saturday%2C%20July%206%2C%202013%2C%20in%20Kansas%20City%2C%20Mo.%3Cp%3EAP%2FCharlie%20Riedel%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BKids%20who%20played%20exclusively%20team%20organized%20sports%20had%20lower%20symptoms%20of%20anxiety%2C%20they%20were%20less%20withdrawn%2C%20and%20they%20had%20fewer%20social%20problems%2C%26quot%3B%20Matt%20Hoffmann%2C%20a%20Cal%20State%20Fullerton%20assistant%20professor%20of%20kinesiology%20and%20the%20leader%20of%20the%20study%2C%20told%20Insider.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20also%20stumbled%20upon%20a%20second%20finding%2C%20one%20Hoffman%20said%20he%20found%20more%20surprising%3A%20Kids%20who%20participated%20in%20individual%20sports%20like%20tennis%20or%20gymnastics%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20face%20mental-health%20challenges%20than%20team%20sports%20participants%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20kids%20who%20played%20no%20sports%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHoffman's%20research%20didn't%20focus%20on%20loneliness%20specifically%2C%20but%20his%20findings%20suggest%20that%20team%20sports%20in%20particular%20%E2%80%94%20which%20generally%20provide%20more%20social%20opportunities%20%E2%80%94%20can%20help%20protect%20young%20people%20from%20feelings%20of%20isolation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20big%20thing%20we%20know%20about%20team%20sports%2C%20especially%20at%20a%20younger%20age%2C%20is%20you%20are%20feeling%20that%20sense%20of%20belonging%20with%20others%2C%20you're%20developing%20friendships.%20We%20need%20that%20social%20aspect%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20get%20kids%20to%20come%20back%20to%20sports%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20say%20several%20factors%20could%20be%20contributing%20to%20a%20decline%20in%20youth-sports%20participation.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprojectplay.org%2Fstate-of-play-2022%2Fparticipation-trends%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESFIA's%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20suggests%20the%20drop-off%20began%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-caused-the-great-recession%5C%22%3E2008%20economic%20downturn%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Great%20Recession%20took%20a%20big%20chunk%20out%20of%20people's%20finances%2C%20including%20municipalities%2C%26quot%3B%20Jon%20Solomon%2C%20the%20editorial%20director%20for%20the%20Aspen%20Institute's%20Sports%20and%20Society%20Program%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BSo%20municipalities%20stopped%20investing%20as%20much%20into%20parks%20and%20recreation%20departments.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cost%20of%20sports%20continues%20to%20be%20a%20challenge%20for%20families%20today.%20The%20average%20family%20spends%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprojectplay.org%2Fstate-of-play-2022%2Fcosts-to-play-trends%5C%22%3E%24883%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20one%20child's%20primary%20sport%2C%20according%20to%20a%202022%20Aspen%20Institute%20survey%2C%20and%20parents%20with%20children%20in%20travel%20leagues%20often%20spend%20much%20more%20%E2%80%94%20as%20much%20as%20%2410%2C000%20per%20year%20%E2%80%94%20Solomon%20said.%20A%20CDC%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F03%2F24%2Fhealth%2Fsports-physical-education-children.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20in%202020%2C%2070%25%20of%20children%20from%20families%20with%20incomes%20above%20roughly%20%24105%2C000%20participated%20in%20sports%2C%20compared%20to%2051%25%20of%20middle-class%20families%20and%2031%25%20of%20those%20at%20or%20below%20the%20poverty%20line.%20The%20YouGov%20survey%20documented%20a%20similar%20trend.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223807%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Colts%20Texans%20Football%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651b1ceb42ecf94db475bdec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222855%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYoung%20people%20typically%20cite%20having%20fun%20and%20playing%20with%20their%20friends%20as%20the%20top%20reasons%20they%20play%20sports%20%E2%80%94%20well%20above%20winning%20or%20chasing%20a%20college%20scholarship.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FDavid%20J.%20Phillip%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESolomon%20said%20the%20%26quot%3Bincreased%20privatization%20of%20youth%20sports%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20marked%20by%20a%20shift%20from%20local%20community%20leagues%20to%20private%20travel%20leagues%20%E2%80%94%20has%20taken%20a%20toll%20on%20sports%20participation%20for%20families%20who%20can't%20afford%20the%20latter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20thinks%20the%20US%20could%20benefit%20from%20%26quot%3Ban%20in-between%20option%26quot%3B%20that%20offers%20quality%20competition%20at%20a%20reasonable%20cost.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20more%20families%20move%20out%20of%20rec%20sports%2C%20it's%20hemorrhaging%20that%20capacity%20for%20the%20local%20community-based%20rec%20leagues%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBoth%20in%20terms%20of%20finances%20because%20fewer%20kids%20are%20playing%2C%20but%20you%20also%20just%20have%20fewer%20volunteers%20who%20can%20officiate%20the%20games%2C%20coach%20the%20teams%2C%20administer%20the%20league.%20So%20it%20all%20sort%20of%20adds%20up.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20there%20are%20also%20some%20kids%20who%20simply%20don't%20want%20to%20play%20sports.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20260%20adults%20surveyed%20by%20YouGov%20whose%20children%20did%20not%20participate%20in%20organized%20sports%20(and%20whose%20children%20were%20old%20enough%20to%20participate)%20listed%20a%20lack%20of%20interest%20as%20the%20primary%20reason%2C%20followed%20by%20financial%20constraints%20and%20the%20time%20commitment%20involved.%20The%20break%20from%20sports%20many%20children%20had%20during%20the%20pandemic%20could%20be%20a%20factor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F8CVBn%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22What%20parents%20say%20are%20the%20reasons%20behind%20their%20children%20not%20being%20involved%20in%20organized%20sports%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20still%20plenty%20of%20children%20who%20have%20an%20interest%20in%20sports%2C%20however%2C%20Solomon%20said%2C%20but%20are%20opting%20out%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons.%20He%20said%20the%20No.%201%20strategy%20for%20the%20Aspen%20Institute's%20Project%20Play%20initiative%20%E2%80%94%20whose%20goal%20is%20to%20boost%20sports%20participation%20%E2%80%94%20is%20for%20communities%20to%20%26quot%3Bask%20kids%20what%20they%20want.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20sounds%20really%20simple%20and%20basic%2C%20but%20unfortunately%2C%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20adults%20actually%20do%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhether%20it's%20parents%20or%20coaches%20or%20administrators%20or%20sports%20providers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221820%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Hooptown%20Youth%20League%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651b1f7f42ecf94db475c20a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221365%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Hooptown%20Youth%20League%20game.%3Cp%3EChris%20Elam%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESolomon%20said%20young%20people%20typically%20cite%20having%20fun%20and%20playing%20with%20their%20friends%20as%20the%20top%20reasons%20they%20play%20sports%20%E2%80%94%20well%20above%20winning%20or%20chasing%20a%20college%20scholarship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20youth-sports%20league%20that%20has%20become%20popular%20in%20Spokane%20%E2%80%94%20and%20helped%20Nancy%20Curtin's%20family%20%E2%80%94%20could%20be%20one%20model%20for%20communities%20to%20follow.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENilson%20said%20any%20group%20thinking%20of%20trying%20a%20similar%20model%20will%20need%20to%20overcome%20forces%20that%20are%20eager%20to%20maintain%20the%20status%20quo%20%E2%80%94%20often%20for%20monetary%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20biggest%20thing%20is%20to%20be%20able%20to%20have%20a%20group%20of%20people%20that%20really%20want%20what's%20best%20for%20kids%20and%20for%20the%20game%20of%20basketball%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurtin%20and%20her%20family%20are%20certainly%20grateful%20for%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHad%20we%20not%20found%20out%20about%20the%20league%20and%20gotten%20involved%2C%20I%20fear%20years%20could've%20gone%20by%20before%20we%20found%20the%20right%20team%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-decline-in-kids-sports-new-model-cheaper-easier-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696760281000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651b208442ecf94db475c3da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-decline-in-kids-sports-new-model-cheaper-easier-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22More%20team%20sports%20could%20help%20kids%20through%20loneliness%2C%20as%20they%20make%20friends%20and%20learn%20skills.%20But%20leagues%20need%20a%20major%20overhaul.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jzinkula%40insider.com%20(Jacob%20Zinkula%2CMadison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floneliness-decline-in-kids-sports-new-model-cheaper-easier-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Floridians%20are%20relocating%20to%20the%20center%20of%20the%20state%20to%20try%20to%20avoid%20hurricanes%20%E2%80%94%20and%20high%20insurance%20premiums%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224189%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rows%20of%20suburban%20homes%20in%20Ocala%2C%20Florida%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6520698b6561dd877e73aed6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223131%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOcala%2C%20Florida%3Cp%3EMichael%20Warren%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EOcala%20has%20the%20lowest%20risk%20of%20coastal%20flooding%20in%20Florida%2C%20analytics%20platform%20Climate%20Alpha%20found.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EOne%20real-estate%20agent%20has%20seen%20an%20influx%20of%20people%20from%20South%20Florida%20seeking%20%26quot%3Bpeace%20and%20security.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EIt's%20an%20emerging%20bright%20spot%20as%20the%20state%20undergoes%20an%20%26quot%3Binsurance%20crisis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Floridians%20are%20leaving%20their%20coastal%20homes%20due%20to%20the%20risk%20of%20extreme%20weather%20events%20and%20increasing%20insurance%20premiums%20%E2%80%94but%20they%20aren't%20going%20too%20far.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20descending%20on%20Ocala%2C%20a%2064%2C000-person%20inland%20town%20located%20centrally%20in%20the%20state%20and%20an%20hour%20drive%20north%20of%20Orlando%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Freal-estate%2Focala-florida-hurricanes-2a991853%3Fmod%3Dreal-estate_lead_story%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%20reports%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Dubbed%20the%20%26quot%3BHorse%20Capital%20of%20the%20World%26quot%3B%20for%20its%20many%20equestrian%20facilities%2C%20the%20small%20town%20is%20now%20a%20hotspot%20for%20those%20who%20want%20to%20stay%20in%20the%20Sunshine%20State%20but%20are%20seeking%20higher%20elevation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20the%20time%20a%20hurricane%20reaches%20us%2C%20they%20lose%20steam%2C%26quot%3B%20Ocala%20real-estate%20agent%20Courtney%20Moody%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20mostly%20a%20rainstorm.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoody%20said%20that%20the%20town's%20reputation%20for%20its%20elevation%20%E2%80%94%20nearly%20100%20feet%20above%20sea%20level%20%E2%80%94%20has%20made%20Ocala%20an%20attractive%20destination%20for%20homebuyers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20like%20the%20sense%20of%20peace%20and%20security%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20it's%20too%20late.%20Moody%20said%20she's%20shown%20houses%20to%20hurricane-stricken%20South%20Floridians%2C%20who%20just%20the%20week%20before%20%26quot%3Bhad%20water%20up%20to%20their%20window%20sills%20inside%20of%20their%20home.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20others%2C%20the%20move%20is%20pre-emptive.%20Recently%2C%20Moody%20worked%20with%20a%20couple%20from%20Miami%20that%20was%20looking%20to%20put%20down%20roots%20for%20a%20family%20and%20were%20attracted%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bstability%26quot%3B%20of%20Ocala.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20couple%20bought%20a%20six-bedroom%20home%20for%20%24950%2C000%20with%20plans%20for%20a%20growing%20family.%20They%20were%20happy%20to%20move%20far%20away%20from%20not%20only%20the%20risk%20of%20extreme%20weather%20events%2C%20but%20also%20the%20rising%20insurance%20premiums%20tied%20to%20coastal%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFlorida's%20going%20through%20an%20insurance%20crisis%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERelief%20100%20feet%20above%20sea%20level%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOcala%20came%20out%20on%20top%20in%20a%20study%20by%20climate-software%20company%20Climate%20Alpha%20for%20the%20Journal.%20It%20evaluated%20Florida%20towns%20based%20on%20federal%20government%20weather%20forecasting%20models%2C%20the%20quality%20of%20local%20infrastructure%2C%20the%20number%20of%20hospital%20beds%20nearby%2C%20and%20other%20factors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EClinching%20the%20spot%20as%20Florida's%20city%20with%20the%20%26quot%3Blowest%20risk%20of%20coastal%20flooding%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Climate%20Alpha%2C%20Ocala%20also%20passed%20with%20flying%20colors%20as%20a%20town%20with%20a%20low%20risk%20of%20flooding%20compared%20to%20other%20inland%20towns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224682%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Cattle%20rancher%20in%20Ocala%2C%20Florida%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652067d79f7ca8b2bbdc7aec%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223511%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOcala%2C%20Florida%3Cp%3EJohn%20Coletti%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20Ocala%20is%20not%20completely%20immune%20to%20hurricanes%2C%20as%20the%20Journal%20noted%202017's%20Hurricane%20Irma%20caused%20some%20power%20outages%20and%20flooding.%20However%2C%20the%20Ocala%20Police%20Department%20told%20the%20outlet%20that%20there%20was%20no%20significant%20damage%20during%20Hurricane%20Idalia%20this%20past%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFloridians%20navigate%20rising%20insurance%20premiums%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EJo%20Anne%20and%20Ed%20Lewis%20used%20to%20get%20%26quot%3Bhunched%20up%26quot%3B%20shoulders%20when%20hurricane%20season%20arrived%20in%20their%20town%20of%20Bonita%20Springs%20on%20the%20west%20coast%20of%20Florida%2C%20the%20Journal%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20seeking%20cover%20from%20a%20hurricane%20this%20past%20August%2C%20they%20happened%20upon%20idyllic%20Ocala%20and%20decided%20to%20make%20a%20new%20inland%20home.%20Significant%20for%20the%20couple%2C%20their%20combined%20deductible%20premium%20%E2%80%94%20one%20for%20home%20damage%20and%20another%20for%20hurricane%20damage%20%E2%80%94%20now%20totals%20%246%2C000%20compared%20to%20the%20%2420%2C000%20for%20their%20home%20in%20Bonita%20Springs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aerial%20view%20of%20downtown%20Ocala%2C%20Florida%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652068329f7ca8b2bbdc7b6a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222160%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOcala%2C%20Florida%3Cp%3EMichael%20Warren%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20average%20insurance%20premiums%20for%20Florida%20residents%20has%20tripled%20in%20the%20past%20five%20years%2C%20according%20to%20Insurance%20Information%20Institute%20data%20collected%20by%20the%20Journal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMajor%20insurers%20have%20cut%20coverage%20in%20the%20state%2C%20as%20the%20increasing%20volatility%20of%20e