e%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22millennial%20man%20at%20work%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651dcd5b617692f0d03f7661%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223671%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Survey%20of%20Working%20Arrangements%20and%20Attitudes%2C%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20surveyed%20working%20men%20work%20hybrid%20schedules.%3Cp%3EHinterhaus%20Productions%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMillennial%20men%20are%20one%20group%20that's%20especially%20swinging%20from%20the%20office%20to%20home%20and%20back%20again.%20According%20to%20data%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwfhresearch.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWFH%20Research%20Project%20and%20the%20Survey%20of%20Working%20Arrangements%20and%20Attitudes%2C%20or%20SWAA%2C%20%3C%2Fa%3Ecompiled%20for%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw28731%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworking%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20provided%20to%20Insider%2C%2027%25%20of%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esurveyed%20working%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emen%20work%20hybrid%20schedules%2C%20compared%20to%2019.5%25%20of%20surveyed%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20millennials%20are%20most%20likely%20to%20be%20working%20hybrid%20schedules.%20About%2028%25%20of%20surveyed%20working%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emillennials%20are%20hybrid%20workers%2C%20according%20to%20that%20survey%20data%2C%20compared%20to%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20Gen%20Zers%20and%2024%25%20of%20those%20aged%2040%20to%2049%20years%20old.%20Just%2016%25%20of%20surveyed%20boomers%20work%20hybrid%20schedules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinkedIn's%20Workforce%20Confidence%20Index%20survey%20found%20similar%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20key%20reason%20for%20millennials'%20decisions%3A%20they're%20the%20generation%20most%20likely%20to%20be%20parents%20with%20young%20children%2C%26quot%3B%20George%20Anders%2C%20an%20editor%20at%20LinkedIn%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20survey%20analysis.%20%26quot%3BAt%20that%20stage%20of%20life%2C%20enjoying%20a%20day%20or%20two%20a%20week%20without%20any%20commute%20time%20is%20a%20big%20plus%20in%20terms%20of%20fitting%20school%20drop-offs%20or%20pickups%20into%20a%20day's%20schedule.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EHybrid%20workers%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20make%20six%20figures%20and%20have%20a%20few%20degrees%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22college%20degree%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5be1d18ee4218a34202c5757%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHybrid%20workers%20tend%20to%20be%20higher%20earners.%3Cp%3EEduardo%20Munoz%20Alvarez%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHybrid%20workers%20tend%20to%20make%20more%20money%20than%20their%20on-site%20counterparts%20and%20tend%20to%20hold%20more%20degrees%2C%20showing%20that%20the%20ability%20to%20work%20from%20home%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esome%20days%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eis%20still%20reserved%20for%20certain%20segments%20of%20the%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fproducts%2Fgao-23-105999%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20American%20Community%20Survey%20data%2C%20nearly%2060%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%20in%20the%20top%2025%25%20of%20earners%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20that%20they%20earn%20at%20least%20%241%2C731%20a%20week%20%E2%80%94%20did%20any%20work%20from%20home%20on%20an%20average%20day%20as%20of%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20according%20to%20the%20SWAA%20data%2C%20nearly%2057%25%20of%20surveyed%20workers%20earning%20over%20%24150%2C000%20are%20hybrid%20workers%2C%20compared%20to%20just%2013.2%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%20who%20are%20earning%20between%20%2410%2C000%20and%20%2420%2C000%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0which%20is%20nearly%20the%20same%20for%20those%20earning%20between%20%2420%2C000%20and%20%2450%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hybrid-work%20wage%20premium%20skyrockets%20once%20workers%20start%20making%20over%20%2450%2C000%3B%2030.2%25%20of%20those%20making%20between%20%2450%2C000%20and%20%24100%2C000%20work%20hybrid%20schedules%2C%20with%20that%20rising%20to%2041.5%25%20for%20those%20surveyed%20who%20make%20between%20%24100%2C000%20and%20%24150%2C000%2C%20according%20to%20SWAA%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20if%20you're%20working%20hybrid%2C%20there's%20a%20higher%20likelihood%20that%20you%20have%20a%20few%20degrees%20on%20your%20wall.%20About%2061%25%20of%20surveyed%20workers%20with%20Ph.D.s%20are%20hybrid%2C%20compared%20to%20about%2037%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%20who%20have%20a%20master's%20or%20professional%20degree%2C%20according%20to%20the%20SWAA%20data.%20Of%20those%20with%20four%20years%20of%20a%20college%20degree%2C%2030.4%25%20work%20remotely%20%E2%80%94%20and%20that%20percentage%20cascades%20down%20with%20the%20less%20formal%20education%20a%20worker%20has%20received.%20About%2012%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%20who%20just%20reached%20a%20high-school%20graduation%20are%20hybrid%2C%20compared%20to%202.3%25%20of%20those%20surveyed%20with%20less%20education%20than%20a%20high-school%20graduation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESome%20industries%20have%20more%20people%20working%20remotely%20at%20least%20some%20of%20the%20time%20than%20others%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FBNBIo%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Establishments%20with%20employees%20teleworking%20some%20of%20the%20time%20by%20industry%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22725%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20it%20comes%20to%20hybrid%20work%2C%20not%20all%20industries%20are%20created%20equal.%20Educational%20services%20was%20the%20industry%20that%20had%20the%20highest%20percentage%20of%20employees%20teleworking%20at%20least%20some%20of%20the%20time%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics.%20That%20industry%20comprises%20roles%20such%20as%20education%20administrators%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20teachers%20and%20instructors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20information%20sector%2C%20which%20comprises%20roles%20such%20as%20data%20processing%2C%20digital%20publishing%2C%20and%20tech%2C%20comes%20in%20a%20close%20second%20among%20industries%20with%20some%20employees%20teleworking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EDon't%20expect%20to%20find%20them%20in%20the%20office%20on%20Fridays%20or%20Mondays%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20in%20a%20wheelchair%20works%20on%20her%20laptop%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63d14c2540fbb600192b6127%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221601%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHybrid%20workers%20don't%20want%20to%20come%20in%20on%20Monday%20and%20Friday.%3Cp%3EPhynart%20Studio%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20hybrid%20workers%20aren't%20completely%20absent%20from%20their%20offices%2C%20don't%20expect%20to%20find%20them%20there%20on%20either%20side%20of%20the%20weekend.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESteven%20Roth%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20major%20New%20York%20City%20private%20landlord%20Vornado%20Realty%20Trust%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freturn-to-office-landlord-friday-dead-forever-hybrid-rto-wfh-2023-5%3Futm_source%3Dlinkedin%26utm_medium%3Dsocial%26utm_campaign%3Dinsider-poll%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehas%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20in-office%20Fridays%20are%20%26quot%3Bdead%20forever%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20in-office%20Mondays%20are%20%26quot%3Btouch-and-go.%26quot%3B%20A%20little%20under%20half%20of%20the%20readers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmondays-fridays-dead-return-to-office-landlord-wfh-rto-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolled%20by%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20LinkedIn%20said%20that%20they%20wouldn't%20go%20into%20the%20office%20on%20Mondays%20and%20Fridays%20%E2%80%94%20and%20just%2029%25%20of%20poll%20participants%20said%20they'd%20go%20in%20on%20one%20of%20those%20days%20but%20not%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20that%20anecdotal%20polling%2C%20office-usage%20data%20backs%20up%20the%20idea%20that%20hybrid%20workers%20might%20be%20starting%20or%20ending%20their%20weekends%20at%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BVery%20few%20people%20are%20coming%20in%20four%20to%20five%20days%20per%20week%2C%26quot%3B%20Anjali%20Grover%2C%20the%20head%20of%20data%20analytics%20at%20Basking%2C%20told%20Insider.%20Basking%2C%20a%20workplace-analytics%20platform%2C%20tracked%20office-utilization%20data%20from%20121%20offices%20across%20the%20world%20in%20April%20through%20June%20of%202023.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20they%20found%20that%20Fridays%20and%20Mondays%20saw%20far%20fewer%20office%20visitors%2C%20with%20offices%20afflicted%20by%20what%20Grover%20calls%20%26quot%3Bempty%20office%20syndrome%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20people%20know%20it'll%20be%20empty%2C%20and%20that%20further%20discourages%20them%20from%20commuting%20in.%20Instead%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20we%20see%20here%20is%20midweek%20peaks%2C%26quot%3B%20with%20workers%20across%20all%20US%20regions%20flocking%20in%20on%20Wednesdays.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%2C%20depending%20on%20where%20they%20are%2C%20you%20might%20barely%20see%20hybrid%20workers%20at%20all.%20While%20workers%20in%20the%20Midwest%20were%20the%20most%20likely%20to%20be%20in%20the%20office%20four%20to%20five%20days%20a%20week%2C%20only%20half%20of%20those%20office%20visits%20lasted%20more%20than%20six%20hours%20%E2%80%94%20suggesting%20that%20even%20the%20most%20in-person%20workers%20are%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Estretching%20the%20limits%20of%20th