0most%20American%C2%A0business%20districts%2C%20Midtown%20is%20heavily%20dependent%20on%20office%20workers%20and%20tourists.%20One%20way%20to%20revive%20it%20is%20to%20make%20it%20a%20place%20more%20people%20call%20home.%20For%20decades%2C%20the%20city's%20zoning%20laws%20have%20made%20it%20illegal%20to%20build%20housing%20in%20large%20parts%20of%20central%20Manhattan.%20Old%20manufacturing%20neighborhoods%20like%20the%20Garment%20District%20are%20no%20longer%20the%20industrial%20powerhouses%20they%20once%20were%2C%20but%20they%20still%20prohibit%20people%20from%20living%20there.%20The%20combination%20of%20office%20vacancies%20and%20a%20severe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-manhattan-real-estate-housing-affordability-no-new-homes-2023-8%5C%22%3Ehousing%20shortage%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20homelessness%20crisis%20have%20put%20pressure%20on%20the%20city%20to%20do%20something%20about%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20healthiest%20business%20districts%20do%20much%20more%20than%20their%20name%20suggests.%20Mixed-use%20office%20districts%20%E2%80%94%20with%20apartments%2C%20a%20range%20of%20retail%2C%20restaurants%2C%20other%20businesses%2C%20public%20spaces%20and%20amenities%20like%20parks%2C%20schools%2C%20and%20libraries%2C%20and%20good%20mass%20transit%20%E2%80%94%20are%20much%20better%20for%20cities.%20And%20New%20York%20City%20has%20had%20success%20transforming%20single-use%20office%20districts%2C%20most%20notably%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftour-inside-building-apartments-from-office-space-2023-9%5C%22%3ELower%20Manhattan's%20financial%20district%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20into%20more%20vibrant%20mixed-use%20places.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMayor%20Eric%20Adams%20wants%20to%20replicate%20that%20success%20in%20Midtown.%20He%20recently%20unveiled%20a%20plan%20to%20rezone%20Midtown%20South%20to%20encourage%20new%20housing%20construction%20and%20the%20conversion%20of%20office%20and%20manufacturing%20spaces%20into%20apartments.%20The%20area%20%E2%80%94%20between%2023rd%20and%2040th%20streets%20and%20Fifth%20and%20Eighth%20Avenues%20%E2%80%94%20is%20home%20to%207%2C000%20businesses%20and%20135%2C000%20jobs%2C%20and%20the%20city%20hopes%20loosening%20the%20zoning%20laws%20will%20spur%20the%20creation%20of%2020%2C000%20new%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDan%20Garodnick%2C%20the%20director%20of%20New%20York%20City's%20Department%20of%20City%20Planning%2C%20told%20Insider%20the%20city%20wants%20Midtown%20South%20to%20become%20%26quot%3Ba%2024%2F7%20live-work%20neighborhood.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20seen%20Midtown%20South%20as%20a%20place%20that%20is%20a%20bit%20out%20of%20whack%20with%20other%20commercial%20districts%20in%20the%20borough%20because%20it%20is%20not%20mixed-use%20in%20character%2C%26quot%3B%20Garodnick%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20saw%20an%20opportunity%20now%20because%20there%20is%20a%20will%20to%20take%20bold%20action%20to%20create%20housing%20and%20to%20think%20about%20ways%20to%20make%20our%20job%20centers%20perform%20even%20better.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECommercial%20business%20districts%20that%20are%20more%20mixed-use%20%E2%80%94%20meaning%20people%20can%20live%2C%20work%2C%20play%2C%20and%20patronize%20a%20range%20of%20businesses%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0are%20much%20healthier.%20And%20converting%20some%20office%20space%20into%20other%20uses%20can%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fmyths-about-converting-offices-into-housing-and-what-can-really-revitalize-downtowns%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eboost%20demand%20for%20commercial%20real%20estate%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20making%20an%20area%20more%20desirable.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20no%20longer%20an%20office%20market%20where%20people%20gravitate%20to%20the%20jobs%2C%20it's%20the%20jobs%20that%20gravitate%20to%20where%20the%20people%20are%20and%20what%20the%20people%20want%2C%26quot%3B%20Lynne%20Sagalyn%2C%20a%20professor%20emerita%20of%20real%20estate%20finance%20at%20Columbia%20University%2C%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMidtown%20has%20some%20of%20the%20world's%20greatest%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moma.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecultural%20institutions%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbroadwaytheaterdistrict.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eentertainment%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cntraveler.com%2Fstory%2Fbest-new-restaurants-in-midtown-nyc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erestaurants%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20shops%2C%20and%20probably%20the%20country's%20best%20mass%20transit%20access.%20Living%20within%20walking%20distance%20from%20these%20attractions%20%E2%80%94%20not%20to%20mention%20your%20office%20%E2%80%94%20is%20a%20strong%20draw%2C%20Sagalyn%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dozens%20of%20high%20end%20luxury%20stores%20remain%20shuttered%20and%20emptied%20after%20six%20months%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20a%20severe%20economic%20downturn%2C%20and%20a%20midtown%20Manhattan%20emptied%20of%20office%20workers%2C%20as%20seen%20on%20September%2020%2C%202020%20along%20Madison%20Avenue%20in%20New%20York%20City's%20Upper%20East%20Side.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651edce06561dd877e71996e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22864%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EStorefront%20businesses%20in%20Midtown%20are%20shifting%20from%20big%20box%20retail%20to%20food%20and%20drink%20establishments.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lichtenstein%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3ENYC%20has%20already%20turned%209-to-5%20neighborhoods%20into%2024%2F7%20locales%2C%20and%20now%20it's%20Midtown's%20turn%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGarodnick%20sees%20Lower%20Manhattan%20as%20an%20example%20of%20how%20to%20transform%20a%20%26quot%3B9-to-5%2C%26quot%3B%20office-dominated%20neighborhood%20into%20a%20more%20vibrant%20community.%20Since%209%2F11%2C%20the%20financial%20district%20has%20more%20than%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fhow-9-11-hastened-downtown-new-yorks-economic-transformation-11631246462%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edoubled%20its%20population%20of%20residents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20attracted%20a%20steadier%20stream%20of%20tourists%2C%20and%20reinvented%20itself%20as%20a%20multi-use%20neighborhood%20with%20a%20mix%20of%20offices%2C%20amenities%2C%20and%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20major%20force%20behind%20Lower%20Manhattan's%20transformation%20was%20significant%20tax%20breaks%20for%20developers%20to%20convert%20office%20buildings%20into%20homes%2C%20and%20incentives%20for%20companies%20to%20relocate%20to%20the%20area.%20Back%20in%201995%2C%20the%20city%20implemented%20a%20generous%20subsidy%20for%20office%20conversions%20that%20helped%20spur%20the%20creation%20of%20more%20than%2012%2C000%20market-rate%20units%20over%20the%20following%2010%20years.%20After%20the%202001%20terrorist%20attacks%2C%20the%20city%20introduced%20another%20incentive%20for%20developers%20to%20build%20and%20convert%20in%20Lower%20Manhattan.%20Now%2C%20about%2020%20million%20square%20feet%20of%20office%20space%20in%20the%20Financial%20District%20has%20been%20turned%20into%2017%2C000%20homes%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nyc.gov%2Fassets%2Fplanning%2Fdownload%2Fpdf%2Fplans-studies%2Foffice-reuse-task-force%2Foffice-adaptive-reuse-study.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20city%20reported%20this%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20incentives%20were%20key%2C%20in%20part%20because%20converting%20office%20buildings%2C%20factories%2C%20or%20other%20commercial%20space%20into%20homes%20can%20be%20both%20practically%20and%20financially%20unfeasible.%20The%20governor%20has%20proposed%20a%2050%25%20property%20tax%20break%20for%20buildings%20that%20include%20a%20certain%20percentage%20of%20units%20for%20lower-income%20residents%20%E2%80%94%20a%20policy%20the%20city%20supports.%20But%20the%20state%20legislature%20hasn't%20passed%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20needs%20to%20be%20appropriate%20incentives%20in%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20Susan%20Mello%2C%20executive%20vice%20president%20and%20group%20head%20of%20capital%20markets%20at%20the%20commercial%20real%20estate%20firm%20Walker%20and%20Dunlop%2C%20told%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20right%20now%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20those%20are%20fully%20fleshed%20out%20in%20the%20mayor's%20plan%20about%20how%20to%20address%20the%20cost%20side%20of%20a%20conversion%2C%20especially%20if%20you're%20trying%20to%20convert%20into%20affordable%20housing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMello%2C%20who%20called%20the%20mayor's%20rezoning%20proposal%20a%20%26quot%3Bgood%20first%20step%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20that%20developers%20also%20need%20to%20be%20convinced%20that%20they%20won't%20face%20too%20many%20bureaucratic%20impediments%20during%20the%20construction%20process.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSponsors%2C%20developers%20would%20need%20to%20see%20that%20the%20city%20is%20really%20engaged%20in%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that%20message%20is%20getting%20all%20the%20way%20through%20the%20entire%20administration%2C%20including%20the%20folks%20that%20are%20issuing%20permits.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20sleeps%20inside%2049th%20Street%20and%20Seventh%20Avenue%20N%2C%20R%20subway%20station%20in%20Midtown%20Manhattan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651ec3409f7ca8b2bbda055f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ELuiz%20C.%20Ribeiro%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3ELiving%20in%20a%20tourist%20hot-spot%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20parts%20of%20Midtown%20that%20are%20already%20bustling%2024%2F7.%20Times%20Square%20is%20one%20of%20those%2C%20according%20to%20Tom%20Harris%2C%20president%20of%20the%20Times%20Square%20Alliance%2C%20which%20represents%20the%20district's%20businesses.%20However%2C%20there%20aren't%20a%20ton%20of%20apartments%20in%20the%20area.%20There%20are%20a%20few%20notable%20exceptions%2C%20including%20the%20glassy%20condo%20tower%20that%20rises%20above%20the%20M%26amp%3BM%20store%20at%201600%20Broadway.%20But%20in%20general%2C%20Harris%20says%20developers%20aren't%20keen%20to%20build%20housing%20in%20the%20tourist-packed%20Square%2C%20though%20he%20would%20welcome%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20not%20negating%20it%2C%20but%20certainly%20the%20opportunities%20south%20of%20Times%20Square%2C%20to%20the%20west%20of%20Times%20Square%2C%20are%20a%20little%20bit%20better%20for%20development%20of%20the%20housing%20stock%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20He%20added%20that%20with%20offices%20being%20converted%20into%20housing%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20Midtown%2C%20demand%20for%20commercial%20space%20will%20hopefully%20rise%20in%20Times%20Square.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mix%20of%20businesses%20around%20Times%20Square%20has%20changed%20in%20a%20way%20that%20could%20be%20appealing%20to%20potential%20residents.%20Retail%20in%20Midtown%20has%20been%20shifting%20away%20from%20big%20box%20stores%20to%20restaurants%2C%20bars%2C%20delis%2C%20and%20bodegas%20for%20several%20years%2C%20Harris%20said.%20Times%20Square%20lost%20179%20businesses%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20but%20has%20since%20welcomed%20more%20than%20180%20new%20businesses%20into%20the%20neighborhood%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Times%20Square%20Alliance.%20And%20those%20new%20businesses%20are%20dominated%20by%20food%20and%20drink%20establishments.%20There%20is%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20offerings%20that%20attract%20a%20diverse%20array%20of%20people%20%E2%80%94%20from%20five-star%20restaurants%20like%20Le%20Bernardin%20and%20the%20Lambs%20Club%20%E2%80%94%20to%20fast-food%20chains%20like%20Popeyes%2C%20Raising%20Cane's%2C%20and%20Taco%20Bell.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20city%20is%20investing%20in%20other%20major%20projects%20in%20Midtown%2C%20including%20the%20newly-opened%20Long%20Island%20Rail%20Road%20commuter%20hub%20at%20Grand%20Central%20Madison%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fny1.com%2Fnyc%2Fmanhattan%2Fnews%2F2023%2F06%2F24%2Fcity-announces-new--broadway-vision--public-spaces%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enew%20pedestrian%20plazas%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20bike%20lanes%20along%20Broadway.%20Another%20major%20policy%20change%20slated%20to%20take%20effect%20sometime%20next%20year%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-congestion-pricing-toll-manhattan-drivers-new-jersey-democrats-commuters-2023-6%5C%22%3Econgestion%20pricing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Traffic%20has%20made%20a%20comeback%20in%20Midtown%2C%20even%20if%20workers%20haven't%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0and%20New%20York%20is%20poised%20to%20impose%20a%20long-debated%20toll%20on%20drivers%20south%20of%2060th%20Street.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGardonick%20argued%20that%20the%20reduction%20in%20traffic%20and%20pollution%20the%20policy%20is%20expected%20to%20bring%20will%20make%20Midtown%20more%20liveable.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20billions%20of%20dollars%20of%20economic%20activity%20lost%20every%20year%20as%20a%20result%20of%20traffic%20and%20congestion%2C%20not%20to%20mention%20the%20headaches%20for%20residents%20when%20they%20hear%20constant%20horn%20honking%20and%20breathe%20the%20fumes%20of%20cars%20that%20can't%20move%20anywhere%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESagalyn%20is%20optimistic%20about%20Midtown's%20future.%20She%20thinks%20some%20amount%20of%20positive%20change%20is%20inevitable%20as%20commercial%20real%20estate%20continues%20its%20downward%20spiral.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20space%20gets%20inexpensive%20enough%2C%20things%20happen%20%E2%80%94%20not%20immediately%2C%20but%20things%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmidtown-manhattan-downtown-crisis-office-apocalypse-urban-doom-loop-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696759021000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651ede066561dd877e719d15%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmidtown-manhattan-downtown-crisis-office-apocalypse-urban-doom-loop-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Midtown%20Manhattan%20is%20in%20desperate%20need%20of%20reinvention.%20More%20mixed-use%20neighborhoods%20could%20be%20the%20answer%2C%20but%20the%20city%20has%20to%20get%20housing%20built.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Eliza%20Relman)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmidtown-manhattan-downtown-crisis-office-apocalypse-urban-doom-loop-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22MCX%20gets%20Sebi%20approval%20to%20launch%20new%20commodity%20derivatives%20platform%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696759007000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-09%2F29%2Ffull%2F1695963781-8564.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fmcx-gets-sebi-approval-to-launch-new-commodity-derivatives-platform-123100800490_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22MCX%20had%20initially%20intended%20to%20introduce%20the%20CDP%20on%20October%203.%20However%2C%20they%20have%20not%20revealed%20the%20new%20launch%20date%20yet%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fmcx-gets-sebi-approval-to-launch-new-commodity-derivatives-platform