2C%20setting%20aside%20the%20findings%20of%20the%20court%20below%20that%20the%20accused%20be%20treated%20as%20major%20and%20be%20tried%20accordingly.%20The%20high%20court%20had%20also%20ordered%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theweek.in%2Fnews%2Fsci-tech%2F2023%2F02%2F15%2Fossification-test-your-age-is-in-your-bones.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThis%2520test%2520involves%2520examining%2520x%2Cuntil%2520the%2520end%2520of%2520adolescence.%5C%22%3Eossification%20test%20%3C%2Fa%3Eof%20the%20accused%20to%20be%20conducted%20by%20the%20Juvenile%20Justice%20Board%2C%20and%20depending%20upon%20the%20report%20of%20the%20Testing%20Authority%2C%20dealing%20with%20the%20accused%20in%20accordance%20with%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20instant%20case%2C%20the%20Juvenile%20Justice%20Board%20(JJB)%20held%20the%20murder-accused%20in%20a%20road%20rage%20case%20to%20be%20a%20juvenile%20on%20September%2019%2C%202014%2C%20finding%20his%20age%20below%2018%20years%20of%20age%20on%20the%20date%20of%20the%20incident%2C%20June%2020%2C%202014.%20The%20father%20of%20the%20deceased%20challenged%20the%20JJB%E2%80%99s%20order%20before%20the%20Court%20of%20Sessions%20Judge%2C%20Mandi%20(Himachal%20Pradesh)%20which%20allowed%20the%20appeal%2C%20setting%20aside%20JJB%E2%80%99s%20order%20with%20a%20direction%20to%20make%20an%20inquiry%20for%20determination%20of%20the%20age%20of%20the%20accused%20and%20thereafter%20to%20proceed%20with%20the%20matter%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThereafter%2C%20another%20order%20was%20passed%20by%20the%20JJB%20on%20May%2026%2C%202017%2C%20again%20finding%20the%20age%20of%20the%20accused%20to%20be%20below%2018%20years%2C%20and%20he%20was%20declared%20as%20juvenile%20in%20conflict%20with%20law.%20The%20father%20of%20the%20deceased%20again%20assailed%20the%20order%20by%20way%20of%20an%20appeal%2C%20and%20in%20terms%20of%20judgment%20dated%20February%2028%2C%202018%2C%20the%20appellate%20court%20set%20aside%20the%20JJB%E2%80%99s%20order%2C%20and%20issued%20directions%20to%20make%20a%20fresh%20inquiry%20for%20determination%20of%20the%20age%20of%20the%20accused%20and%20to%20proceed%20with%20the%20matter%20thereafter.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20accused%2C%20Shiv%20Kumar%20alias%20Shivam%2C%20filed%20a%20criminal%20revision%20petition%20before%20the%20high%20court%2C%20alleging%20that%20he%20was%20not%20heard%20by%20the%20appellate%20court%20before%20passing%20the%20order%20on%20February%2028%2C%202018.%20The%20high%20court%20set%20aside%20the%20order%20of%20the%20appellate%20court%2C%20directing%20it%20to%20hear%20the%20matter%20afresh%20after%20hearing%20the%20accused.%20Upon%20remand%2C%20the%20appellate%20court%20again%20set%20aside%20the%20JJB%E2%80%99s%20order%20dated%20May%2026%2C%202017%2C%20and%20directed%20the%20Board%20to%20make%20an%20inquiry%20for%20determination%20of%20the%20age%20of%20the%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20accused%20challenged%20this%20judgment%20by%20way%20of%20a%20criminal%20revision%20petition%20before%20the%20high%20court%20which%20set%20aside%20the%20findings%20returned%20by%20the%20appellate%20court%20on%20April%2024%2C%202019%2C%20with%20a%20direction%20to%20decide%20the%20appeal%20strictly%20in%20accordance%20with%20law.%20On%20November%2020%2C%202021%2C%20the%20appellate%20court%20again%20set%20aside%20the%20JJB%E2%80%99s%20order%20and%20held%20the%20accused%20to%20be%20an%20adult.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFacts%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20father%20of%20the%20deceased%20alleged%20before%20the%20high%20court%20that%20the%20date%20of%20birth%20of%20the%20accused%20was%20mentioned%20in%20the%20matriculation%20certificate%20as%20June%2014%2C%201997.%20Section%2049%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Frepealed-act%2Frepealed_act_documents%2FA2000-56.pdf%5C%22%3EJuvenile%20Justice%20(Care%20and%20Protection%20of%20Children)%20Act%2C%202000%3C%2Fa%3E%20lays%20down%20that%20where%20it%20appears%20to%20the%20competent%20authority%20that%20person%20brought%20before%20it%20under%20any%20of%20the%20provisions%20of%20this%20Act%20is%20a%20juvenile%20or%20the%20child%2C%20it%20shall%20make%20due%20inquiry%20so%20as%20to%20the%20age%20of%20person%20so%20brought%20before%20it%2C%20which%20shall%20be%20deemed%20to%20be%20the%20true%20age%20of%20that%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20Rule%2012.3%20of%20the%20Juvenile%20Justice%20(Care%20and%20Protection%20of%20Children)%20Rule%2C%202007%2C%20the%20age%20determination%20inquiry%20is%20to%20be%20conducted%20by%20the%20Court%20or%20the%20Board%20or%20as%20the%20case%20may%20be%2C%20the%20Committee%20by%20seeking%20evidence%20by%20obtaining%20matriculation%20or%20equivalent%20certificates%2C%20if%20available%2C%20and%20in%20the%20absence%20whereof%2C%20the%20date%20of%20birth%20certificate%20from%20the%20school%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20argued%20before%20the%20high%20court%20that%20since%20the%20matriculation%20certificate%20of%20the%20accused%20was%20available%2C%20the%20date%20mentioned%20therein%20was%20to%20be%20construed%20as%20sacrosanct%2C%20and%20this%20was%20lost%20sight%20of%20by%20the%20appellate%20court%20while%20allowing%20the%20appeal.%20It%20was%20urged%20that%20the%20appellate%20court%20did%20not%20appreciate%20that%20the%20factum%20of%20date%20of%20birth%20of%20the%20accused%20being%20June%2014%2C%201997%2C%20it%20was%20also%20corroborated%20by%20other%20documents%2C%20Aadhaar%20Card%2C%20voter%20card%20and%20school%20record.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20also%20argued%20before%20the%20high%20court%20that%20there%20was%20some%20discrepancy%20with%20regard%20to%20name%20of%20the%20accused%2C%20as%20his%20name%20is%20Shivam%20Chaudhary%20and%20not%20Shiv%20Kumar%20and%20the%20documents%20relied%20upon%20by%20the%20appellate%20court%20were%20relating%20to%20Shiv%20Kumar%20and%20not%20the%20accused%2C%20whose%20name%20is%20Shivam%20Chaudhary.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20father%20of%20the%20deceased%2C%20who%20is%20a%20respondent%20in%20the%20case%2C%20submitted%20to%20the%20high%20court%20that%20there%20is%20a%20variation%20in%20the%20date%20of%20birth%20of%20the%20accused%20as%20recorded%20in%20the%20matriculation%20certificate%20as%20compared%20to%20the%20record%20of%20the%20school%20and%20the%20record%20of%20the%20Gram%20Panchayat.%20Besides%2C%20it%20has%20been%20alleged%20that%20criminal%20proceedings%20stand%20initiated%20against%20the%20parents%20of%20the%20accused%20as%20also%20the%20school%20management%20for%20forging%20with%20the%20admission%20record%20of%20the%20accused%20in%20the%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20found%20that%20the%20appellate%20court%20had%20not%20taken%20into%20consideration%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20documents%20in%20which%20date%20of%20birth%20of%20the%20accused%20is%20June%2014%2C%201997%20were%20existing%20before%20the%20date%20of%20the%20incident%2C%20so%20it%20cannot%20be%20assumed%20that%20there%20was%20some%20tinkering%20with%20the%20date%20of%20birth%20therein%2C%20so%20that%20the%20accused%20could%20be%20shown%20as%20a%20minor%20after%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20relied%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F190473838%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ERishipal%20Singh%20Solanki%20vs%20State%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2021)%20and%20others%20in%20which%2C%20it%20was%20held%20that%20Section%2094%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fhandle%2F123456789%2F2148%3Fsam_handle%3D123456789%2F1362%5C%22%3EJuvenile%20Justice%20(Care%20and%20Protection%20of%20Children)%20Act%2C%202015%20%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20akin%20to%20Section%2049%20of%20the%202000%20Act%20raises%20a%20presumption%20regarding%20juvenility%20of%20the%20age%20of%20the%20child%20brought%20before%20the%20JJB%20or%20the%20Committee.%20However%2C%20in%20case%20the%20Board%20or%20Committee%20has%20reasonable%20ground%20for%20doubt%2C%20it%20can%20undertake%20the%20process%20of%20determination%20of%20age%20by%20seeking%20evidence.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20held%20that%20the%20presumption%20has%20to%20be%20drawn%20on%20observation%20of%20the%20child.%20The%20evidence%20can%20be%20in%20the%20form%20of%20date%20of%20birth%20certificate%20from%20the%20school%20or%20the%20matriculation%20certificate%20from%20the%20Board%20concerned%2C%20if%20available.%20In%20the%20absence%20thereof%2C%20the%20birth%20certificate%20given%20by%20a%20Corporation%20or%20by%20a%20Municipal%20Authority%20or%20a%20Panchayat%20can%20be%20relied%20upon.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20above%2C%20the%20age%20has%20to%20be%20determined%20by%20an%20ossification%20test%20or%20any%20other%20medical%20age%20determination%20test.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20held%20that%20ossification%20test%20will%20put%20to%20rest%20any%20controversy%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20age%20of%20the%20accused%20as%20on%20the%20date%20when%20the%20offence%20took%20place%20and%20the%20test%20would%20carry%20more%20authenticity%20in%20the%20light%20of%20there%20being%20documents%20which%20are%20giving%20contradictory%20dates%20of%20the%20age%20of%20the%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20found%20that%20whereas%20there%20is%20no%20tinkering%20with%20the%20documents%20in%20terms%20whereof%20the%20accused%20was%20a%20major%20as%20on%20the%20date%20when%20the%20incident%20took%20place%2C%20there%20is%20an%20overwriting%20etc%20in%20some%20of%20the%20documents%2C%20benefit%20of%20which%20is%20being%20claimed%20by%20the%20accused%20to%20put%20forth%20his%20contention%20that%20he%20was%20a%20minor%20on%20the%20date%20of%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696758024000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F25222448%2FSupreme-Court-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fossification-test-of-a-juvenile-declared-as-adult-on-th