20that%20the%20police%20also%20took%20her%20laptop%20and%20mobile%20phone%20and%20asked%20her%20to%20report%20to%20their%20office%20in%20New%20Delhi%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPaul%20had%20worked%20for%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%20from%202018%20to%202022%20and%20was%20currently%20a%20researcher%20with%20the%20National%20Platform%20For%20the%20Rights%20of%20the%20Disabled.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECriticising%20the%20raid%20on%20%3Cem%3ENewsClick%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Kerala%E2%80%99s%20chief%20minister%2C%20Pinarayi%20Vijayan%2C%20called%20it%20a%20fascist%20measure%20meant%20to%20gag%20the%20independent%20press.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696681514000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F07130338%2FUntitled-design-2021-02-10T154651.122.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdelhi-police-seize-laptop-and-phone-of-former-newsclick-journalist-in-kerala%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Anusha%20Paul%2C%20a%20former%20NewsClick%20journalist%2C%20was%20asked%20about%20the%20funding%20and%20her%20reporting%20assignments%20during%20her%20time%20with%20the%20organisation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A15%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fdelhi-police-seize-laptop-and-phone-of-former-newsclick-journalist-in-kerala%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Courts%20Should%20Deal%20With%20Cases%20Related%20to%20Crimes%20Against%20Women%20in%20a%20Realistic%20Manner%3A%20SC%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20on%20October%206%20(Friday)%20said%20that%20courts%20should%20deal%20with%20cases%20related%20to%20crimes%20against%20women%20in%20a%20realistic%20manner%2C%20and%20not%20allow%20the%20criminals%20to%20escape%20on%20account%20of%20procedural%20technicalities%2C%20perfunctory%20investigation%2C%20or%20insignificant%20lacunas%20in%20the%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EA%20bench%20of%20Justices%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%20and%20Prashant%20Kumar%20Mishra%20made%20these%20remarks%20while%20dismissing%20an%20appeal%20filed%20by%20a%20man%2C%20against%20his%20conviction%2C%20who%20failed%20to%20explain%20what%20had%20happened%20to%20his%20wife%2C%20who%20died%20due%20to%20poisoning.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20said%20that%20although%20the%20appellant-convict%20tried%20to%20project%20a%20picture%20that%20as%20soon%20as%20his%20wife%20fell%20sick%2C%20he%20immediately%20took%20her%20to%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Sanjay%20Gandhi%20%5BMemorial%5D%20Hospital%2C%20there%20is%20no%20evidence%20in%20this%20regard%2C%20the%20bench%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20appellant-convict%20was%20expected%20to%20lead%20some%20evidence%20as%20to%20what%20had%20transpired%20at%20Sanjay%20Gandhi%20Hospital.%20He%20has%20maintained%20complete%20silence.%20It%20is%20only%20the%20appellant-convict%20who%20could%20have%20explained%20in%20what%20circumstances%20and%20in%20what%20manner%20he%20had%20taken%20his%20wife%20to%20the%20hospital%20and%20who%20attended%20his%20wife%20at%20the%20hospital.%20If%20it%20is%20his%20case%20that%20his%20wife%20was%20declared%20dead%20on%20being%20brought%20to%20the%20hospital%2C%20then%20it%20is%20difficult%20to%20believe%20that%20the%20hospital%20authorities%20allowed%20the%20appellant%20to%20carry%20the%20dead%20body%20back%20home%20without%20completing%20the%20legal%20formalities%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Justice%20Pardiwala.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20said%20that%20there%20is%20sufficient%20circumstantial%20evidence%20to%20enable%20the%20prosecution%20to%20invoke%20Section%20106%20of%20the%20Evidence%20Act%20(w%3Cspan%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehen%20any%20fact%20is%20especially%20within%20the%20knowledge%20of%20any%20person%2C%20the%20burden%20of%20proving%20that%20fact%20is%20upon%20him%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E)%20and%20shift%20the%20burden%20on%20the%20accused%20husband%20to%20explain%20what%20had%20actually%20happened%20on%20the%20date%20his%20wife%20died.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20word%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9Cespecially%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20bench%20explained%2C%20means%20facts%20that%20are%20preeminently%20or%20exceptionally%20within%20the%20knowledge%20of%20the%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESection%20106%20is%20an%20exception%20to%20Section%20101%20of%20the%20Evidence%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESection%20101%20lays%20down%20the%20general%20rule%20that%2C%20in%20a%20criminal%20case%2C%20the%20burden%20of%20proof%20is%20on%20the%20prosecution%2C%20and%20Section%20106%20is%20by%20no%20means%20intended%20to%20relieve%20it%20of%20that%20duty.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20contrary%2C%20the%20bench%20said%20that%20Section%20106%20is%20designed%20to%20address%20specific%20exceptional%20circumstances%20in%20which%20it%20might%20be%20impossible%20or%2C%20at%20the%20very%20least%2C%20excessively%20burdensome%20for%20the%20prosecution%20to%20substantiate%20facts%20that%20are%20%E2%80%9Cespecially%20within%20the%20knowledge%20of%20the%20accused%20and%20which%20he%20can%20prove%20without%20difficulty%20or%20inconvenience.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ECiting%20several%20cases%2C%20the%20bench%20held%20that%20the%20court%20should%20apply%20Section%20106%20of%20the%20Evidence%20Act%20in%20criminal%20cases%20with%20care%20and%20caution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20cannot%20be%20said%20that%20it%20has%20no%20application%20to%20criminal%20cases.%20The%20ordinary%20rule%20which%20applies%20to%20criminal%20trials%20in%20this%20country%2C%20that%20the%20onus%20lies%20on%20the%20prosecution%20to%20prove%20the%20guilt%20of%20the%20accused%2C%20is%20not%20in%20any%20way%20modified%20by%20the%20provisions%20contained%20in%20Section%20106%20of%20the%20Evidence%20Act%2C%E2%80%9D%20observed%20the%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20clarified%20that%20Section%20106%20cannot%20be%20invoked%20to%20make%20up%20for%20the%20inability%20of%20the%20prosecution%20to%20produce%20evidence%20of%20circumstances%20pointing%20to%20the%20guilt%20of%20the%20accused.%20This%20section%20cannot%20be%20used%20to%20support%20a%20conviction%20unless%20the%20prosecution%20has%20discharged%20the%20onus%20by%20proving%20all%20the%20elements%20necessary%20to%20establish%20the%20offence%2C%20it%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20further%20clarified%20that%20the%20onus%20does%20not%20shift%20to%20the%20accused%20until%20a%20prima%20facie%20case%20is%20established%20by%20such%20circumstantial%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESection%20106%20pertains%20to%20cases%20where%20the%20accused%E2%80%99s%20guilt%20is%20established%20based%20on%20the%20evidence%20presented%20by%20the%20prosecution%2C%20unless%20the%20accused%20can%20provide%20additional%20facts%2C%20particularly%20within%20their%20knowledge%2C%20that%20would%20negate%20the%20prosecution%E2%80%99s%20evidence%2C%20the%20bench%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20such%20a%20scenario%2C%20if%20the%20accused%20provides%20an%20explanation%20that%20is%20reasonably%20true%20considering%20the%20proven%20circumstances%2C%20they%20benefit%20from%20the%20principle%20of%20reasonable%20doubt%2C%20even%20if%20they%20cannot%20prove%20the%20truth%20of%20their%20explanation%20beyond%20a%20reasonable%20doubt%2C%20said%20the%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20the%20accused%20fails%20to%20provide%20any%20explanation%20or%20provides%20a%20false%20or%20untenable%20explanation%2C%20this%20alone%20may%20turn%20the%20scale%20against%20them%2C%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20present%20case%2C%20considering%20the%20proved%20facts%2C%20the%20bench%20said%20it%20is%20unable%20to%20speculate%20about%20any%20alternative%20theory%20which%20is%20compatible%20with%20the%20innocence%20of%20the%20accused.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20bench%20reduced%20the%20sentence%20of%20the%20deceased%E2%80%99s%20mother-in-law%2C%20who%20is%20convicted%20only%20for%20the%20offence%20punishable%20under%20Section%20498-A%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(dealing%20with%20punishment%20for%20husband%20or%20his%20relative%20subjecting%20a%20woman%20to%20cruelty)%2C%20to%20the%20period%20already%20undergone.%20As%20she%20is%20on%20bail%2C%20the%20bench%20said%20she%20is%20not%20required%20to%20surrender%20at%20the%20moment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20argued%20that%20courts%20should%20approach%20cases%20related%20to%20women%20in%20a%20more%20realistic%20manner.%20Otherwise%2C%20it%20could%20lead%20to%20criminals%20being%20encouraged%20while%20discouraging%20the%20victims%20due%20to%20the%20lack%20of%20punishment%20for%20the%20crimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696679117000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcourts-should-deal-with-cases-related-to-crimes-against-women-in-a-realistic-manner-sc%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Courts%20should%20not%20allow%20the%20criminals%20to%20escape%20on%20account%20of%20procedural%20technicalities%2C%20perfunctory%20investigation%2C%20or%20insignificant%20lacunas%20in%20the%20evidence%2C%20the%20top%20court%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcourts-should-deal-with-cases-related-to-crimes-against-women-in-a-realistic-manner-sc%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Unprecedented%20Hamas%20attack%20on%20Israel%20has%20caused%20crisis%20-%20and%20there%20are%20days%20of%20war%20ahead%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696678620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F768x432%2Fskynews-rocket-strike-hamas_6311922.jpg%3F20231007070020%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Funprecedented-hamas-attack-on-israel-has-caused-crisis-and-there-are-days-of-war-ahead-12978991%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Hamas%20operation%20started%20just%20before%207am%20in%20Israel%20and%20came%20without%20any%20warning.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A307%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Funprecedented-hamas-attack-on-israel-has-caused-crisis-and-there-are-days-of-war-ahead-12978991%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Funprecedented-hamas-attack-on-israel-has-caused-crisis-and-there-are-days-of-war-ahead-12978991%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Funprecedented-hamas-attack-on-israel-has-caused-crisis-and-there-are-days-of-war-ahead-12978991%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Corruption%20Shadow%20Over%20Candidate%20Shortlisted%20for%20Top%20Job%20in%20Railway%20Finance%20PSU%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F05%2F28145254%2F13286908034_bb8f865649_h.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Ministry%20of%20Railways%20is%20expected%20to%20conduct%20a%20set%20of%20interviews%20to%20fill%20the%20post%20of%20the%20chairman%20and%20the%20chief%20managing%20director%20(CMD)%20of%20its%20public%20sector%20unit%20(PSU)%2C%20the%20Indian%20Railway%20Finance%20Corporation%20(IRFC)%2C%20this%20Monday%2C%20on%20October%209.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20post%20has%20been%20vacant%20for%20a%20year%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EQuestionable%20record%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20previous%20IRFC%20CMD%20and%20chairman%2C%20Amitabh%20Banerjee%2C%20was%20divested%20of%20his%20duties%20%E2%80%9Cwith%20immediate%20effect%E2%80%9D%20in%20October%202022.%20This%20happened%20after%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fthe-wire-impact-railways-finance-commission-amitabh-banerjee%5C%22%3Especial%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20Railway%20Board%20and%20the%20Vigilance%20Directorate%20of%20the%20Railways%20had%20confirmed%20a%20full%20term%20for%20Banerjee%20in%20spite%20of%20a%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI)%20FIR%20naming%20him%20in%20a%20multi-crore%20corruption%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20learnt%20that%20the%20list%20of%20shortlisted%20candidates%20for%20the%20top%20post%20at%20IRFC%20to%20replace%20Banerjee%20includes%20an%20officer%2C%20Shelley%20Verma%2C%20who%20has%20held%20the%20post%20of%20the%20director%20(finance)%20at%20the%20PSU%20for%20some%20years%20now.%20She%20has%20also%20temporarily%20assumed%20the%20charge%20of%20the%20CMD.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EVerma%2C%20however%2C%20is%20a%20controversial%20name%2C%20and%20her%20presence%20in%20the%20shortlist%20has%20raised%20both%2C%20eyebrows%20and%20questions.%20This%20is%20as%20she%2C%20in%20her%20capacity%20as%20director%20(finance)%2C%20had%20given%20monetary%20approval%2C%20on%20various%20occasions%20during%20her%20predecessor%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20tenure%2C%20to%20procure%20gold%20and%20silver%20medallions%20worth%20lakhs%20to%20allegedly%20gift%20%E2%80%98dignitaries%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESuch%20financial%20approvals%20were%20allegedly%20given%20by%20her%20in%20spite%20of%20the%20Central%20Vigilance%20Commission%E2%80%99s%20standing%20rules%20stating%20that%20PSUs%20are%20discouraged%20from%20giving%20expensive%20gifts%20to%20%E2%80%98dignitaries%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20no%20government%20official%20is%20allowed%20to%20accept%20any%20gifts%20during%20occasions%20such%20as%20Diwali%2C%20New%20Year%E2%80%99s%20Eve%2C%20Christmas%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOfficial%20gave%20approval%20to%20procure%20expensive%20%E2%80%98gifts%E2%80%99%20between%202020%20and%202021%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20government%20rules%20permit%20giving%20gifts%20only%20to%20promote%20commercial%20or%20business%20interests%2C%20a%20top%20railway%20official%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Frailway-finance-commission-amitabh-banerjee-vigilance%5C%22%3Ehad%20told%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%20October%202022%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20has%20never%20been%20any%20need%20for%20the%20IRFC%20to%20bribe%20clients%20to%20give%20loans%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20in%20lieu%20of%20an%20interest%20in%20private%20entities%20to%20build%20wagons%2C%20rolling%20stocks%2C%20etc.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20official%20had%20spoken%20in%20connection%20with%20a%20case%20filed%20by%20the%20Railway%20vigilance%20department%20against%20then%20%E2%80%98IRFC%20employees%E2%80%99%2C%20including%20Banerjee%2C%20on%2030%20counts.%20These%20included%20allegations%20of%20financial%20misappropriation%20amounting%20to%20%E2%80%9C%2427%2C000%E2%80%9D%2C%20having%20spent%20as%20%E2%80%9Centertainment%20allowance%E2%80%9D%20to%20buy%20%E2%80%9Cexpensive%20watches%2C%20mobile%20phones%2C%20laptops%2C%20gold%20coins%2C%20expensive%20shawls%2C%20etc.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFollowing%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20exit%2C%20the%20Railway%20vigilance%20department%20noted%20the%20procurement%20of%20expensive%20gifts%20like%20gold%20and%20silver%20medallions%2C%20and%20pendants%2C%20from%20the%20Minerals%20and%20Metals%20Trading%20Corporation%20(MMTC)%2C%20during%20his%20term%2C%20prompting%20an%20inquiry.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThese%20official%20approvals%20to%20procure%20dozens%20of%20medallions%20(mementos)%20between%202020%20and%202021%20were%20allegedly%20given%20by%20Verma.%20These%20approvals%20under%20question%20have%20been%20perused%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETop%20IRFC%20officials%20fail%20to%20provide%20the%20list%20of%20beneficiaries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20vigilance%20inquiry%2C%20top%20IRFC%20officials%2C%20including%20Banerjee%2C%20failed%20to%20provide%20the%20list%20of%20%E2%80%98dignitaries%E2%80%99%20who%20were%20recipients%20of%20the%20gold%20and%20silver%20medallions%2C%20pendants%20and%20bars%2C%20costing%20lakhs%20of%20public%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20learnt%20recently%20that%20two%20independent%20members%20of%20the%20Railway%20Board%20whom%20IRFC%20officials%20had%20claimed%20to%20have%20gifted%20gold%20medallions%20denied%20receiving%20any%2C%20thus%20putting%20the%20needle%20of%20suspicion%20on%20the%20top%20officials%2C%20including%20the%20then%20CMD.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20board%20members%20denied%20receiving%20any%20such%20gifts%20during%20the%20vigilance%20probe.%20In%20addition%2C%20IRFC%20officials%20failed%20to%20provide%20the%20list%20of%20beneficiaries%2C%20and%20thereby%2C%20how%20the%20PSU%20benefitted%20from%20it.%20Therefore%2C%20%E2%80%9Cofficials%20of%20IRFC%20including%20Amitabh%20Banerjee%E2%80%9D%20came%20under%20the%20scanner%20for%20alleged%20embezzlement%20of%20public%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECBI%20files%20corruption%20case%20in%20August%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20February%202023%2C%20the%20Vigilance%20Directorate%20of%20the%20Railways%20wrote%20to%20the%20CBI%20director%20to%20investigate%20the%20matter.%20On%20August%2028%2C%20the%20CBI%2C%20taking%20note%20of%20the%20request%20made%20by%20Bhaskar%20Roy%20Choudhury%2C%20joint%20director%20Vigilance%20(Intelligence)%20Railway%20Board%2C%20filed%20an%20FIR%20in%20Delhi%20under%20various%20sections%20of%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20seen%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20CBI%20FIR%2C%20which%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%5BThe%5D%20Vigilance%20Railway%20Board%20scrutinised%20two%20files%20of%20%5Bthe%5D%20IRFC%20and%20recorded%20statement%20and%20revealed%20serious%20irregularities%20with%20respect%20to%20procurement%20and%20distribution%20of%20gold%20and%20non-gold%20items.%20The%20extent%20of%20embezzlement%20is%20not%20provided%20in%20the%20complaint.%20The%20complaint%20alleged%20that%20private%20persons%20are%20also%20involved.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20further%20says%20%E2%80%9Csubstantive%20offences%E2%80%9D%20have%20been%20stacked%20up%20against%20Banerjee%20and%20%E2%80%9Cother%20unknown%20public%20servants%20and%20unknown%20private%20persons%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShelly%20Verma%20is%20not%20named%20by%20the%20CBI%20in%20the%20August%2028%20case.%20The%20FIR%20has%20named%20only%20IRFC%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20Banerjee%20would%20have%20cleared%20the%20dubious%20purchases%2C%20which%20necessarily%20would%20have%20involved%20Verma%2C%20who%2C%20as%20mentioned%20earlier%2C%20was%20director%20(finance)%20at%20the%20PSU.%20That%20is%20why%20her%20name%20among%20the%20shortlisted%20candidates%20is%20questionable.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20Banerjee%E2%80%99s%20case%2C%20too%2C%20while%20multiple%20instances%20of%20alleged%20corrupt%20practices%20and%20misuse%20of%20public%20money%20for%20personal%20gain%20was%20being%20investigated%20against%20him%2C%20the%20ministry%20and%20the%20Railway%20Board%20continued%20to%20keep%20him%20in%20the%20top%20post%20of%20the%20PSU%2C%20till%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20published%20its%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Frailway-finance-commission-amitabh-banerjee-vigilance%5C%22%3EExclusive%3A%20Rail%20Ministry%20Overlooked%20CBI%20FIR%20Against%20Key%20PSU%20Head%20Named%20for%20Causing%20Rs%20144%20Crore%20Loss%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETill%20then%2C%20as%20the%20PSU%E2%80%99s%20head%2C%20Banerjee%20was%20taking%20financial%20decisions%20on%20its%20behalf%20and%20had%20the%20right%20to%20seek%20foreign%20exchange%20from%20the%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20green%20signal%20to%20Shelley%20Verma%E2%80%99s%20credentials%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20order%20to%20be%20able%20to%20hold%20the%20post%20of%20the%20CMD%20for%20a%20full%20term%2C%20the%20Vigilance%20Directorate%20of%20the%20Railways%20would%20also%20have%20to%20grant%20a%20green%20signal%20to%20Verma%E2%80%99s%20professional%20credentials%20and%20integrity.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhat%20is%20baffling%20is%2C%20while%20the%20railway%20vigilance%20department%20has%20found%20alleged%20embezzlement%20of%20funds%20due%20to%20an%20act%20in%20which%20Verma%20was%20closely%20involved%2C%20she%20has%20been%20allowed%20by%20the%20ministry%20and%20the%20Railway%20Board%2C%20thus%20far%2C%20to%20continue%20in%20the%20post%20of%20temporary%20CMD.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%20October%205%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20emailed%20a%20set%20of%20queries%20to%20the%20Union%20minister%20of%20Railways%2C%20Ashwini%20Vaishnaw%3B%20chairman%20and%20chief%20executive%20officer%20of%20the%20Railway%20Board%2C%20Jaya%20Verma%20Sinha%3B%20Anjali%20Goel%2C%20member%20(Finance)%20at%20the%20Railway%20Board%3B%20and%20Shobhana%20Bandopadhyay%2C%20principal%20executive%20director%20(vigilance)%20at%20the%20Railway%20Board%2C%20seeking%20answers%20to%20why%20an%20official%20under%20the%20scanner%20for%20alleged%20financial%20embezzlement%20has%20been%20shortlisted%20for%20the%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAmong%20other%20questions%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20asked%20whether%20she%20has%20been%20granted%20vigilance%20clearance%20to%20hold%20the%20post%2C%20and%20also%20why%20she%20was%20appointed%20to%20temporarily%20take%20charge%20of%20the%20CMD%20in%20the%20first%20place%2C%20even%20after%20the%20CBI%20had%20filed%20a%20corruption%20case%20on%20the%20matter%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20story%20will%20be%20updated%20as%20and%20when%20they%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696678243000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F05%2F28145254%2F13286908034_bb8f865649_h.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22